1777943490212211	ward-dev	itc:v3:AWLk-eSZPknJ0AAAAAAAQevvVr6uuAAAAAEtBA		item.create	bn-1vno	{"description":"## Summary\n\nWhile coordinating Ward Rust Unsafe Phase 2 work, a subagent hit a maw failure running a read-only `git diff` inside a stale workspace that had uncommitted rule work. `maw exec` failed before the command could complete:\n\n```text\nError: git stash create failed (exit code 1): error: could not write index\n```\n\nThis blocked the worker from reviewing/committing already-tested changes and required tech-lead intervention.\n\n## Reproduction Context\n\nRepo: `/home/bob/src/ward`\nWorkspace: `phase2-layout-rule`\nState at failure:\n\n```text\nWorkspace 'phase2-layout-rule' is behind the current epoch, but has uncommitted changes.\n M crates/ward-rust-uoe/src/rules/mod.rs\n?? crates/ward-rust-uoe/src/rules/layout_cast.rs\n?? crates/ward-rust-uoe/tests/rule_layout_cast.rs\n```\n\nThe worker had already run the focused test successfully:\n\n```bash\nmaw exec phase2-layout-rule -- cargo test -p ward-rust-uoe --test rule_layout_cast -- --nocapture\n# 7 passed\n```\n\nThen this read-only inspection command failed:\n\n```bash\nmaw exec phase2-layout-rule -- git diff -- \\\n  crates/ward-rust-uoe/src/rules/layout_cast.rs \\\n  crates/ward-rust-uoe/src/rules/mod.rs \\\n  crates/ward-rust-uoe/tests/rule_layout_cast.rs\n```\n\nObserved error:\n\n```text\nError: git stash create failed (exit code 1): error: could not write index\n```\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nOne of these should happen:\n\n- `maw exec` should allow read-only commands like `git diff` to run in stale dirty workspaces without attempting an auto-stash/sync path; or\n- if auto-stash is required for correctness, maw should preserve work and report an actionable workspace-state error before invoking git stash; or\n- if `git stash create` fails, maw should include enough context to explain what index/path operation failed and how to recover.\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\n`maw exec` surfaced a low-level `git stash create` failure (`could not write index`) while running a read-only command. The workspace work was not lost, but the agent had to stop because project instructions were to stop on maw issues.\n\n## Why This Matters\n\nThis hits a common multi-agent path:\n\n1. Worker creates a workspace from epoch N.\n2. Tech lead merges another workspace, advancing epoch.\n3. Worker's workspace becomes stale but still has uncommitted changes.\n4. Worker tries to inspect its diff before commit.\n5. `maw exec <workspace> -- git diff ...` fails due stash/index handling.\n\nThe failure mode is especially costly because it appears during review/commit hygiene, after tests have already passed.\n\n## Suggested Investigation\n\n- Check whether `maw exec` is attempting auto-sync or user-work replay setup before all commands, including read-only git commands.\n- Check stale+dirty workspace handling: read-only commands should probably skip stash/index mutation.\n- Check whether untracked files in the pathspec contribute to `git stash create` failing.\n- Add a regression test for stale dirty workspace + `maw exec <ws> -- git diff -- <tracked> <untracked>`.","kind":"bug","labels":["maw-exec","stale-workspace","dirty-workspace","git-index"],"size":"m","title":"maw exec git diff fails with git stash create / could not write index in stale dirty workspace"}	blake3:SNS2YWBbwj4TZHNbz_xoc-xOaphDRMT9meZ5CN_st0o
