1778864854571279	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy2g0		item.create	bn-17o1	{"description":"stash_impl::worktree_state_commit uses raw write_blob instead of the default-on LFS clean filter (write_blob_with_path), so for LFS-tracked workspaces the materialized state/recovery ref stores full content instead of pointers and diverges from 'git stash create'. Same class for .gitattributes text/eol(CRLF)/custom filters. Conditional on non-maw repo config (maw's own repo has no LFS/.gitattributes) so deferred from the bn-uyk3 fresh-eyes pass. Found by fresh-eyes review of gix migration post v0.60.9.","kind":"task","labels":["tracking"],"title":"fix(gix): worktree_state_commit bypasses LFS clean filter & .gitattributes CRLF"}	blake3:PlKQjuGq_41vtDLLXXQiuMGxuWB2Q8_1q4tJjQvsVWM
1778864854845869	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy2w0		item.create	bn-29x0	{"description":"merge.rs force_checkout_fallback -> checkout_impl::remove_stale_files removes every worktree path absent from the target tree, incl. untracked files. git checkout --force (the replaced cmd) preserves untracked files. On the snapshot-FAILED branch there is no recovery ref, so this is a new data-loss surface vs the prior CLI. Fix: preserve untracked (capture_before_destroy best-effort, or a preserve_untracked flag). Found by fresh-eyes review of gix migration post v0.60.9.","kind":"task","labels":["tracking"],"title":"fix(gix): force_checkout_fallback deletes untracked files git checkout -f would keep"}	blake3:p9cokoJCudUED4KEzxpzg69btL9PdFqd8ukwVUL91es
1778864855119153	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy3A0		item.create	bn-2b9h	{"description":"recover.rs grep_snapshot Matcher::Regex uses Rust regex crate; replaced 'git grep -e' which uses POSIX BRE. Saved BRE patterns (a\\+, \\(x\\|y\\), foo\\{2,3\\}) now match differently or fail; recovery search (last line of defense) silently returns wrong/zero hits. Also: grep_snapshot emits a phantom trailing empty line vs git grep (LOW). Decide: document dialect change loudly, or keep a git-grep carve-out for the regex branch. Found by fresh-eyes review of gix migration post v0.60.9.","kind":"task","labels":["tracking"],"title":"fix(gix): recover --search --regex changed BRE->Rust regex dialect"}	blake3:yD_n96gzRQaKYNhNIf5jeV7Nz7sl1tyLODwcVPVuFCo
1778864855397251	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy3Q0		item.create	bn-36id	{"description":"maw-git refs_impl::atomic_ref_update classifies CAS failure by substring-matching gix error Display text; ignored integration test atomic_ref_update_conflict proves create-only (MustNotExist) CAS maps to BackendError not RefConflict. Masked today by maw-core non-atomic pre-check + single-writer invariant, but wrong under a true concurrent first-op race. Fix: match the typed gix variant, broaden map_git_error rescue, un-#[ignore] the test. Found by fresh-eyes review of gix migration post v0.60.9.","kind":"task","labels":["tracking"],"title":"fix(gix): atomic_ref_update CAS classified by fragile error-string match; un-ignore test"}	blake3:jqoNIVZiW83ihILnrv_NKPkgK4Dk0QdfZBlQPwNePYU
1778867061651282	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy3g0		item.create	bn-35mr	{"description":"sync_ff_paths_in_worktree/ff_apply_one_path and sync_target_worktree_to_epoch use Path::exists() to guard the Ok(None) deletion of an FF-absorbed path. exists() follows symlinks, so a path that is currently a DANGLING symlink (e.g. a stale .bones/events shard link) returns false and is NOT removed — diverging from the git reset --keep / git checkout the gix migration (bn-3lcl) replaced, and inconsistent with the symlink-aware symlink_metadata().is_ok() pattern used in stash_apply (stash_impl.rs:396) and ff_materialize_blob. Leaves a stale dangling symlink that the next merge snapshot can re-inject as an untracked addition, undoing an epoch deletion. Fix: use full.symlink_metadata().is_ok() at merge.rs:2927 and merge.rs:3160.","kind":"task","labels":["gix","fresh-eyes"],"title":"fix(gix): FF-absorb deletion skips dangling symlinks (exists() vs symlink_metadata)"}	blake3:_lmXBwLSesCW0gNxd8U-P4rktZoRwIhkx_UkP6N4sr0
