1778892114761491	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy7w0		item.create	bn-2l00	{"description":"REPRO (stress test in /tmp): create two ws from same epoch, merge one (epoch advances), then a stale ws with committed work gets 'maw ws sync <ws> --rebase' which records a structured rebase conflict (conflict markers committed to its HEAD).\n\nOBSERVED inconsistency across commands for the SAME conflicted workspace:\n- 'maw ws status'   -> '<ws>  epoch:... [conflicted: 1 rebase conflict(s)]'  (correct)\n- 'maw ws conflicts <ws>' -> lists src/lib.rs, 'Error: embedded conflict markers detected in workspace HEAD(s)' (correct)\n- 'maw ws list'     -> '<ws>  /path (ready to merge)' AND prints 'Merge ready: maw ws merge <ws> --into default --destroy'  (WRONG)\n- 'maw ws merge <ws> --into default' -> 'Error: Workspace <ws> has 1 unresolved conflict(s)' (correctly gated)\n\nIMPACT: maw targets context-free agents (AGENTS.md output guidelines: every message must stand alone, copy-paste commands must work). An agent reading 'maw ws list' will run the suggested '--destroy' command and hit a guaranteed failure; worse, the suggestion includes --destroy. ws list must reflect the conflicted state (e.g. '(conflicted: N — resolve before merge)') and must NOT emit a 'Merge ready' line for workspaces whose HEAD contains unresolved conflict markers. Reproduced consistently (alice and bob workspaces, separate runs). No data loss.","kind":"bug","title":"ws list reports rebase-conflicted workspace as 'ready to merge' (contradicts ws status / merge gate)"}	blake3:qD_vjRpoXIgTQ-ID4skgvXgFYycmBtuERnsG-vtFJ4A
1778892127606179	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy8A0		item.create	bn-2wyh	{"description":"REPRO (stress test in /tmp): start 'maw ws merge <ws> --into default', kill -9 the process during the BUILD phase (simulates OOM/panic/Ctrl-C/power loss).\n\nOBSERVED: '.manifold/merge-state.json' (phase:build, frozen_heads, epoch_before recorded) is left on disk. Every subsequent merge — any workspace — fails permanently with:\n  'Error: PREPARE: merge already in progress (merge-state file exists)'\n\nRecovery gaps (all confirmed):\n1. No 'maw ws merge --abort', '--resume', '--reset', or '--continue' subcommand exists.\n2. 'maw ws merge --force' does NOT bypass it (force targets a different check).\n3. 'maw doctor' reports 'All checks passed!' — does NOT detect or mention the orphaned merge-state.\n4. The error message gives NO recovery path (violates AGENTS.md output guideline: errors must include the exact command to fix).\n5. Only fix is manually 'rm .manifold/merge-state.json' — undocumented internal-layout knowledge; impossible for a context-free agent (maw's target audience).\n\nSEVERITY: high availability/UX. A single interrupted merge bricks the merge pipeline for all agents until manual intervention. Prime Invariant itself is NOT violated (epoch unchanged since kill was pre-COMMIT; after manual rm, retry merged all 200 files with correct content — no data loss).\n\nSUGGESTED FIX: stale-merge-state detection + recovery. The state file already has phase + frozen_heads + epoch_before, enough to support 'maw ws merge --abort' (clear state; safe iff phase < commit / epoch unchanged) and/or '--resume'. doctor should flag an orphaned merge-state (e.g. process not alive / older than N min) with the exact recovery command. The 'merge already in progress' error should print that recovery command inline.","kind":"bug","title":"Crashed/interrupted merge wedges ALL future merges — no abort/resume, doctor blind, no recovery guidance"}	blake3:reUvPoH9dZVDXFC4Exssd0Y0yWqKQLERo08K5R5B0cw
1778892200410242	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy8Q0		item.create	bn-3bbc	{"description":"REPRO (stress test in /tmp): launch N concurrent 'maw ws create dupe --from main' for the SAME name.\n\nOBSERVED (non-deterministic, reproduced at N=4 and N=5):\n- ALL N processes exit 0 and print the full success banner ('maw ws merge dupe --into default --destroy' / 'The merge engine captures changes when merging'). Only one workspace's worktree actually persists; the others are silently clobbered. (N=5 run: 5/5 claimed success, should be 1.)\n- Timing-dependent end state: one run left 'dupe' as 'MISSING — fix: maw ws destroy dupe --force' and 'maw doctor' -> 'Some checks failed' (MISSING worktree(s): dupe). Another run converged to a single consistent workspace but still all 5 lied about success.\n\nROOT CAUSE: 'maw ws create' does check-exists-then-create with no per-name lock (classic TOCTOU). The existence guard ('Error: invalid/exists') only triggers when serialized; under a real race every caller passes the check and proceeds.\n\nIMPACT: maw's entire purpose is coordinating concurrent agents. An orchestrator dispatching the same workspace to two agents (or an agent retrying create) can: (a) corrupt workspace metadata (MISSING worktree, doctor failure, needs 'destroy --force'), and (b) make multiple agents each believe they own a workspace that was actually clobbered by another -> later work/edits land in a worktree that gets overwritten. Note: '.manifold/locks/' exists and the merge path already uses a proper mutex (merge-state file) — workspace-create just doesn't take a lock.\n\nSUGGESTED FIX: take an exclusive per-workspace-name lock (under .manifold/locks/) around the create's existence-check + worktree-add + metadata-write so concurrent same-name creates serialize; the loser must get a clear 'already exists' error, not a false success banner. No data-loss in this test (fresh empty workspaces) but the atomicity gap is the concern.","kind":"bug","title":"Concurrent 'maw ws create <same-name>' is a TOCTOU race: all callers report success, worktrees silently clobbered, state may corrupt"}	blake3:xLBK0GcRnpkmr3ACcaMsnJrgQxnQCF_TsoBUcGZZUvY
