1778961174587401	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEygA4		item.create	bn-7kg3	{"description":"## Summary\n`crates/maw-git/src/status_impl.rs::count_dirty_tracked` adds 1 per index\nentry with `stage_raw() != 0`. A conflicted path occupies 3 index entries\n(stages 1/2/3, no stage-0), so one conflicted file is counted as 3 in the\n`maw status` status-bar \"N changed\" count. `git status --porcelain` reports\nsuch a path once (`UU path`).\n\n## Severity: low (cosmetic)\nStatus-bar count only; the default workspace (merge target) rarely has\nconflict entries. Not a Prime-Invariant issue. Pre-existing: introduced in\ncommit 2462032f (2026-04-03, before v0.60.9), unchanged by the gix migration.\n\n## Fix (already implemented + tested)\nDedupe contiguous conflict-stage entries via a single remembered path\n(index is sorted by (path, stage), so a path's stages are contiguous —\nallocation-free, no behavior change for the non-conflicted hot path). Adds\na deterministic regression test (`count_dirty_tracked_counts_conflicted_path_once`)\nthat creates a real merge conflict and asserts the count is 1, not 3.\n\nVerified in the prior review session: full maw-git lib suite 32 passed / 0\nfailed; clippy + fmt clean for the changed file. Patch saved at\n/tmp/count_dirty_fix.patch.\n\n## Origin\nFound during the post-v0.60.9 fresh-eyes gix-migration review (out of strict\nscope then; the user asked to route it through the normal bone/workspace flow\nrather than leave it uncommitted in ws/default).","kind":"bug","title":"count_dirty_tracked triple-counts conflicted (stage>0) index entries in status-bar count"}	blake3:ECRIKxeEU-HwFDIILe5sj58CX1sx5qAvDNH_SZo3KR4
1778961182229734	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEygQ4		item.move	bn-7kg3	{"state":"doing"}	blake3:fSTyL0i_ZDoE0Lifgd9u9vGA-pE1t4HL4-kLq_3E5Pc
1778961182242298	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEygg4		item.assign	bn-7kg3	{"action":"assign","agent":"maw-dev"}	blake3:V9vZrLlUsu6XeVusRe5Fql-4OTYp2MN4nDx7ql-Tfi4
1778964114095701	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEygw4		item.create	bn-142y	{"description":"# maw v1.0 — North Star\n\nv1.0 is the release where the author will recommend maw to others, because the\ntwo confidence gaps are closed WITH EVIDENCE, not hope:\n\n1. Prime Invariant proven (no committed work is ever lost) — via a\n   continuously-run adversarial DST harness with two machine-checked oracles\n   (work-loss + state-coherence), not hand-testing.\n2. Agent ergonomics proven (agents drive maw >= bare git-worktrees, > jj under\n   concurrency) — via a real-agent benchmark across a benign->hostile\n   condition spectrum, presented as dominance (NOT a composite score),\n   including the regime where maw is overkill.\n\nRolled into v1.0 (was tentatively v1.1): the layout decoupling — normal\ncheckout at repo root that doubles as merge target, agent worktrees hidden\nunder .maw/ (Claude Code .claude/ precedent) — gated on a pre-registered\nergonomics eval showing no agent regression.\n\n## Hard gates to cut v1.0\n- DST Oracle A (no work lost) AND Oracle B (state coherence) clean over target\n  soak volume; bn-cm63 + the prior lost-commits incident encoded as permanent\n  regression seeds.\n- Agent-ergonomics eval with PRE-REGISTERED pass/fail; results published\n  including the regime where maw loses/overkills.\n- Layout decision resolved: merge layout into v1.0 iff its pre-registered eval\n  shows no regression; else v1.0 ships on the trust artifact alone and layout\n  is the immediate follow-up. Layout must NOT block the trust artifact; the\n  launch must NOT ship without it.\n\n## Non-goals\n- Speed/throughput benchmarking (perf is not why anyone picks maw; author-run\n  perf wins are low-trust).\n- Hiding plain git from agents in the inner loop (agents are git-fluent; maw\n  owns only the coordination boundary).","kind":"goal","labels":["v1-0"],"size":"xl","title":"maw v1.0: recommendable with evidence — Prime Invariant proven, agent ergonomics proven, layout decoupled"}	blake3:9P6A2HHdDy08L7GrVmjNJpf9kI9rlk-a3K2wOpJ2wS4
1778964213145632	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyhA4		item.create	bn-mg1a	{"description":"Probe bone to learn the from-file schema. Tests {braces}, (parens),\nand `backticks` survive without shell eval.\n","kind":"goal","labels":["probe"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"s","title":"PROBE goal (delete me)"}	blake3:Up1IZgkCj8GtXwfFDZUpK165EEY2MKOyYuHNMNjR0Ys
1778964255662119	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyhQ4		item.create	bn-3nw1	{"description":"Continuously-run deterministic simulation harness. Random valid\nop-sequences over N workspaces + fault injection (incl. process kills via\nFP_* failpoints) + two machine-checked oracles, seed-deterministic with\nfailing-seed shrinking.\n\nOracle A (no committed work lost): every commit ever reachable from any\nworkspace ref is still reachable from (default history) UNION (recovery\nrefs) UNION (extant workspace refs).\nOracle B (state coherence): no dangling head refs, merge-state consistent\nwith refs, no orphaned recovery. Must catch bn-cm63-class bugs (bn-cm63\nwas NOT a work-loss bug — it was a coherence bug doctor caught).\n\nBuilt on existing primitives: maw-assurance (oracle/model/trace), the\nFP_* failpoints, recovery refs, the merge-state FSM. ~70% of the substrate\nalready exists; the missing 30% is the top-level generator+driver+oracle\nloop. THIS SUB-GOAL IS THE HARD GATE for cutting v1.0.\n","kind":"goal","labels":["v1-0","dst"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"xl","title":"SG1: Prime-Invariant adversarial DST harness (the trust instrument)"}	blake3:lJDXjEcsZLjduOm7B91kZHtXSJ3uAIvjWDOWsHla1m0
1778964255892433	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyhg4		item.create	bn-2jwi	{"description":"Real-agent driver over the SAME scenario generator as SG1's DST.\nSubstrate adapters: maw, git-worktrees+thin-convention, jj-workspaces.\nMetrics recorded per-run and NEVER composited into a score: tool-calls,\nturns-to-done, work-lost events, work-redone / wasted-turns, human\ninterventions.\n\nSweep a benign->hostile condition spectrum; the HEADLINE is the crossover\npoint (below it maw is overkill; above it alternatives lose work / jj\nopfork-wedges). Present as dominance, and publish the regime where maw\nloses — that is what immunizes it from \"author marketing\".\n\nDoubles as the diagnostic for maw's OWN ergonomic weak points: attribute\nwasted turns per maw verb/state -> prioritized fix list feeding SG4.\nPre-register pass/fail + methodology BEFORE running.\n","kind":"goal","labels":["v1-0","benchmark"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"xl","title":"SG2: Agent-ergonomics benchmark + diagnostic (maw vs git-worktrees vs jj)"}	blake3:hg3aJJnqUqeElSyZTDIhn4dJgp_DxGiBvXBjrEmJJ8Q
1778964256129837	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyhw4		item.create	bn-2yh1	{"description":"Decouple the merge/recovery value from the bare-repo ws/ layout opinion:\nrepo root becomes a normal checkout that doubles as the merge target;\nagent worktrees move under a hidden .maw/ (Claude Code .claude/\nprecedent). The engine already has the privileged-root-checkout update\npath (sync_target_worktree_to_epoch / FF-absorb) — reuse it. The agent\nguardrail (\"go to your workspace, do not edit root files\") relocates from\nthe LAYOUT to the path handed to the agent + AGENTS.md + an optional guard\nhook.\n\nGATED on a pre-registered ergonomics eval (subset of SG2) showing no agent\nregression vs the current layout. Rolled from v1.1 into v1.0 because\nlaunching v1.0 on the adoption-blocking ws/ layout spends the one first\nimpression on the exact friction stopping recommendations today.\n","kind":"goal","labels":["v1-0","layout"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"xl","title":"SG3: Layout decoupling — normal root checkout + hidden .maw/ worktrees"}	blake3:L-I5pP7zgahzaBq71vEfasANPiNxkhKgojAPH0CD1sQ
1778964256365606	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyiA4		item.create	bn-2j45	{"description":"Closes confidence gap #2 (\"agent ergonomics unparalleled — not sure\nyet\"). Failure asymmetry: worktrees/jj LOSE or WEDGE work; maw PRESERVES\nbut may cost recovery turns. So maw's interesting metric is \"turns wasted\nfighting maw's own conflict/stale/recovery model\", not \"work lost\" (~0 by\ndesign via the Prime Invariant).\n\nTake SG2's prioritized friction list (likely: structured-conflict\nworkspace UX, stale-workspace state legibility, the --abort/retry flow,\nmaw's own verb scarcity vs self-describing-output mitigation) and harden\nthe highest-cost verbs/states, then re-run the SG2 benchmark to confirm\nreduction vs pre-registered targets. Blocked by SG2's diagnostic output.\n","kind":"goal","labels":["v1-0","ergonomics"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"l","title":"SG4: Agent-ergonomics hardening (driven by the SG2 diagnostic)"}	blake3:yuQelIjqCv6Fw4hW5TPazL6bb-M7pS2AvtFzWcE7IKs
1778964256604802	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyiQ4		item.create	bn-3ctu	{"description":"Acceptance-criteria doc encoding the hard gates. Publication: the\nsafety-evidence writeup (two invariants, soak volume, the bn-cm63\nself-found-bug SCAR story — lead with the scar, not the trophy),\nreproducible harness + public seeds; the crossover-curve writeup\n(explicitly including the regime where maw is NOT worth it);\ndocs/README/AGENTS.md updates for the new layout; version bump +\nCHANGELOG; release cut gated by the acceptance criteria. Blocked by SG1\n(trust gate), the SG3 layout decision, and SG4.\n","kind":"goal","labels":["v1-0","release"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"l","title":"SG5: v1.0 release & publication artifact"}	blake3:sub72u7Fr-YZxnSBAd_zjx18Ff5g5kNdubYb6mquxaw
1778964377979345	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyig4		item.create	bn-26mv	{"description":"Architecture doc: scenario generator + fault injection + Oracle A + Oracle\nB + shrinker. Inventory and map maw-assurance (oracle/model/trace), the\nFP_* failpoints, recovery refs, and the merge-state FSM to the missing\ntop-level loop. Formally state both oracles as checkable predicates.\nDone when: doc reviewed; the ~30% missing surface is enumerated as the\nother SG1 tasks.\n","kind":"task","labels":["v1-0","dst"],"parent":"bn-3nw1","size":"m","title":"T1.1 Design DST architecture + inventory existing primitives"}	blake3:hT5eCuyBkASW_iz4WBpMB8SFP_ZihII00sl6xBL4C9A
1778964378211208	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyiw4		item.create	bn-a2i2	{"description":"Generate random VALID op-sequences over N workspaces (create/edit/commit/\nmerge/sync/destroy/recover). Parameterized condition spectrum: concurrency\ndegree, mid-op kill probability, overlapping-edit rate, stale-workspace\nrate. Fully deterministic from a seed. This is the SHARED substrate also\nconsumed by SG2's agent benchmark — design the interface accordingly.\nDone when: a seed reproduces an identical op-sequence + condition profile.\n","kind":"task","labels":["v1-0","dst"],"parent":"bn-3nw1","size":"l","title":"T1.2 Scenario + condition generator (shared substrate)"}	blake3:AEk0esCz0-K5qwSyd6mSVviGXYz1iT1bS6YMD4zOmZ8
1778964378437304	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyjA4		item.create	bn-1qqu	{"description":"After every step, assert: every commit ever reachable from any workspace\nref is still reachable from (default history) UNION (recovery refs) UNION\n(extant workspace refs). Track the historical set across the run. Done\nwhen: deliberately injecting a work-loss bug is caught with a minimal\nseed.\n","kind":"task","labels":["v1-0","dst"],"parent":"bn-3nw1","size":"l","title":"T1.3 Oracle A — no committed work lost (reachability)"}	blake3:XTuA7nVmVHqvpYIq1chPkAf84UFjA1QAwDDQe40AuKw
1778964378669254	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyjQ4		item.create	bn-3j43	{"description":"After every step, assert: no dangling refs/manifold/head/* for\nnon-existent workspaces; merge-state.json consistent with refs; no\norphaned recovery. Must catch bn-cm63-class coherence bugs (bn-cm63 lost\nno work but was a real coherence defect doctor caught). Done when: a\nsynthetic bn-cm63 reproduction is flagged by the oracle.\n","kind":"task","labels":["v1-0","dst"],"parent":"bn-3nw1","size":"m","title":"T1.4 Oracle B — state coherence"}	blake3:fLS2BQGazPpDFxYLnSdafikscZ774pJSZYYj6TrO1wQ
1778964378907333	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyjg4		item.create	bn-1mtr	{"description":"Drive faults through the existing FP_* failpoints AND real process kills\nat COMMIT CAS boundaries, cleanup, and prepare. Need an env/IPC bridge to\nset failpoints from the harness (today they are set programmatically under\n--features failpoints with no external bridge). Done when: the harness can\ndeterministically crash a merge at any named phase.\n","kind":"task","labels":["v1-0","dst"],"parent":"bn-3nw1","size":"m","title":"T1.5 Fault injection via FP_* incl. process kills"}	blake3:SD4a-7fhJLmYHJ7kTpwwBzH8Jt3pCRjzWytK18XOWPo
1778964379139862	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyjw4		item.create	bn-1rct	{"description":"Seed replay must be bit-exact. On an oracle violation, shrink the\nop-sequence to a minimal reproducing case and emit it. Done when: a\nplanted bug reduces to a <10-step minimal seed automatically.\n","kind":"task","labels":["v1-0","dst"],"parent":"bn-3nw1","size":"m","title":"T1.6 Determinism + failing-seed shrinker"}	blake3:1Ps_dMSQ2sdDXvJtONcC34e5wIpOT-r_R5aKZ70hqbM
1778964379372285	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEykA4		item.create	bn-3f1r	{"description":"Bounded DST budget every commit; long nightly soak. On failure, surface\nseed + minimized trace as a CI artifact. Done when: CI runs it and a\nplanted regression fails the build with an actionable seed.\n","kind":"task","labels":["v1-0","dst"],"parent":"bn-3nw1","size":"m","title":"T1.7 CI integration (bounded per-commit + nightly soak)"}	blake3:pTMwddpY0qmupj3Ad92an0sKHIqiaRuXef2OaIJ0fO8
1778964379619740	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEykQ4		item.create	bn-3rx7	{"description":"Encode bn-cm63 and notes/incident-lost-commits-2026-02-05.md as permanent\nmust-catch seeds. CI fails if either oracle would no longer catch them.\nDone when: removing the bn-cm63 fix makes the corpus run go red.\n","kind":"task","labels":["v1-0","dst"],"parent":"bn-3nw1","size":"s","title":"T1.8 Regression seed corpus (bn-cm63 + lost-commits incident)"}	blake3:UYU-CU5b5vsLiWpb8juOagQR4EqHKSlmhlSAGi-Z4o4
1778964379859020	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEykg4		item.create	bn-k23k	{"description":"Define the target volume (proposal: >= 1e9 fault-injected op-steps across\nthe condition spectrum) and run it. Record machine-checked\nzero-violation-of-A-and-B evidence for the v1.0 publication. Gates the\nrelease (blocks SG5).\n","kind":"task","labels":["v1-0","dst"],"parent":"bn-3nw1","size":"m","title":"T1.9 Soak campaign + published zero-violation evidence"}	blake3:CeLFOoqol-Sh81vr0MfhPCZ7grQGRgHINrf56tEMD_M
