1779056974840007	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy9w8		item.comment	bn-3qxi	{"body":"SP2 PASS. Key finding: Oracle A MUST be CONTENT(blob)-reachability, NOT commit-ancestry (ancestry false-positives every merge -- maw rebuilds trees; proven empirically). Spec: A = every authored blob in W stays in U(frontier); B = B1 no-dangling head/<ws> + B2 owned-ref symmetry + B3 merge-state coherence + B4 recovery well-formed. Harness: both planted defects trip EXACTLY their oracle; B agrees with maw doctor. Cost: B ~2.7ms/step O(1)-in-N (fine); naive A O(history)->O(N^2) UNACCEPTABLE at 1e6 -> MANDATED incremental reachable-set design for bn-1z8q (amortized <=1ms/step). Deliverable: ws/bn-3qxi/notes/oracle-ab-spec.md. Not merged; lead reviews."}	blake3:8BBk1QJxzJFO99SNk72lnhW-REZF6DmaL5SAmvjoD7M
1779057019053288	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy-A8		item.move	bn-3qxi	{"state":"done"}	blake3:EfcVdXMa-BgqGvbrcc4BSTU2igUwfQ9SGMcyL0dBbT4
1779057039745531	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy-Q8		item.comment	bn-1z8q	{"body":"SP2 (bn-3qxi) handoff — see notes/oracle-ab-spec.md §0,§2,§6. LOAD-BEARING: Oracle A MUST be blob/content reachability, NOT commit-ancestry. The existing oracle.rs::check_g1_reachability does commit-ancestry — proven to false-positive on every merge (maw rebuilds the merged tree). Re-spec G1 to blob-content reachability or add a new Oracle-A check and demote G1. ALSO: naive per-step rev-list is O(N^2) (~days at 1e6 steps) — incremental live reachable-set + lazy-confirm design is MANDATORY (budget ~1ms/step amortized). This makes T1.3 harder than originally scoped — budget the incremental design as a sub-task."}	blake3:5B85cL9S4FSMVlv9tY-KuXODYPDyeF0-NqF3oeX8Szg
1779057039813210	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy-g8		item.comment	bn-3ji6	{"body":"SP2 (bn-3qxi) handoff — see notes/oracle-ab-spec.md §3,§6. Oracle B = B1-B4 coherence predicate, O(1)-in-N (low risk, no incremental design). Implement B1-B4; REUSE maw_core::refs::workspace_owned_refs (B2) and maw_core::merge_state::{MergeStateFile,staleness} for the live-merge guard (B1/§3.1) — do NOT re-derive (keeps oracle and ref_gc GC guard from diverging). Batch B4 via git cat-file --batch-check. Self-test: synthetic bn-cm63 state must trip B1 and agree with maw doctor's verdict."}	blake3:nNq8YxB-iYrb9ZwYFqaLDucoaEbCxAbSc5SLcI_JQws
1779057231832944	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy-w8		item.create	bn-1cww	{"description":"src/merge/commit.rs::fp_commit is declared const fn but its #[cfg(feature=\"failpoints\")] body calls the fallible fp!() macro. cargo build --features failpoints fails to compile on current Rust (E0015/E0658/E0493, Try/FromResidual not const). Effect: ALL FP_COMMIT_* failpoints (incl FP_COMMIT_BETWEEN_CAS_OPS, the most dangerous boundary) are uncompilable dead code; no DST harness can use them. One-line fix: drop the const qualifier (zero-cost; no-feature body is Ok(()) and inlines). Found by SP1/bn-imw8. Fix applied in ws/bn-imw8. bn-263u depends on this.","kind":"task","labels":["dst"],"title":"fp_commit const fn breaks --features failpoints build"}	blake3:W-DLymQRozPzcMfTY1St5HuqSXa9tNvYZPFE1Eca69c
1779057302341957	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy_A8		item.comment	bn-imw8	{"body":"SP1 done. Recommend HYBRID: in-proc workhorse (bit-exact w/ pinned git dates, ~24 seq/s, faults via failpoints::set, no new mech) + small faithful subprocess tier (real SIGKILL, ~120x slower, the only crash-recovery proof). Failpoint mech: ADD MAW_FP env bridge to failpoints.rs (in-proc needs none; subprocess sleep-window can only hit ONE phase). Found+fixed pre-existing build-breaker: commit.rs fp_commit const fn made --features failpoints uncompilable -> COMMIT failpoints were dead code (tracked bn-1cww; bn-263u depends on fix). maw-assurance ~75% reusable. ADR+prototype in ws/bn-imw8 (commit 7b9ca0c1). Two faithful-only findings (sleep-window blind spot; zombie-masked liveness) -> faithful tier non-optional for the gate."}	blake3:4y1e9xWE1ofpFd0XhpaZfXmXxOfYqaGaxDHq1b82n0w
