1779061909031145	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyihA		item.comment	bn-1z8q	{"body":"Size bumped l->xl: SP2 (bn-3qxi) AND T1.1 (bn-kwm7) independently found T1.3 is heavier than 'implement G1' — it must (1) re-spec/replace the proven-wrong commit-ancestry check_g1_reachability with blob/content reachability, and (2) implement the MANDATORY incremental W/U live-set design (naive is O(N^2) ~ days at 1e6 steps; budget amortized <=1ms/step, lazy full rev-list only on suspected violation). Spec: notes/oracle-ab-spec.md §0,§2,§2.1 + notes/sg1-dst-architecture.md §4.1."}	blake3:5wf5m4wWNXrrS3mwzJ-jkjudZIFkkiJ2XYCv2aip80A
1779061909105847	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyixA		item.comment	bn-1f53	{"body":"T1.1 (bn-kwm7) fixes your interface contract — see notes/sg1-dst-architecture.md §2. The generator MUST emit a driver-agnostic *plan stream* (ScenarioGenerator::generate(seed,profile)->ScenarioPlan; no maw/git calls, never links the FSM) so SG1's in-proc driver AND SG2/T2.1's real-agent driver consume the SAME bytes per seed ('build once, drive two ways'). PlannedStep MUST carry a seed-derived git_time (GIT_AUTHOR_DATE/COMMITTER_DATE) — the determinism contract is mandatory (§5) and T1.6 tests it. Stable types in §2.1 are the cross-SG contract; don't diverge."}	blake3:Q6WrEVCHkOBPaXKOT42sAQ5MDCue389b2Y0vwEkNZFc
1779061918261867	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyjBA		item.comment	bn-2ftq	{"body":"T2.7 DONE (not merged/closed — lead handles). Frozen @ 2026-05-17T23:48:34Z, committed 72eabf6 in ws/bn-2ftq, strictly before T2.2(bn-1sqo)/T2.6(bn-3l1f) (both still open). Deliverable: notes/sg2-benchmark-preregistration.md. Frozen bars: SG3 gate T3.5 = work_lost==0(hard) + wedge-rate <=+0.10abs + turns/tool-calls <=x1.15 + interventions no-increase (any miss = NO-GO=acceptable, ships SG1-only). SG4 T4.3 = wasted-turns>=30%down on top-3 verbs + hostile median-turns>=15%down + work_lost stays 0(hard) + no wedge regression. Non-composite: 2-axis per-condition table + stacked-panel crossover figure, C0 overkill regime shipped not clipped. Double-investment bias named + bound (mechanical layout decision, no author override; loss-regime publish committed). 8 of 10 numeric bars are honestly-labeled pre-registered decision rules not SP3 measurements (ledger S7, R1-R8) — only work_lost==0 + jj-wedge-direction are SP3/Prime-Invariant grounded. Reviewers: check S7."}	blake3:gkRn1A2n7Tpya_a3Ub4bUS1MMGI2QSqkqrErJfmkvME
1779061944346038	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyjRA		item.comment	bn-tmt8	{"body":"T3.1 design landed: notes/sg3-layout-design.md (ws/bn-tmt8, commit fbbbff3). Grounded in SP4 #1-13: 12 trivial-relocation specced as path/predicate edits, #9 (un-bare live root + v2->new migration) specced as a 14-step crash-safe maw migrate reusing existing snapshot/ANCHOR/replay/recovery machinery. KEY: SP4's '~12' join(ws) sites is actually ~84 across 27 files (uniform shape) -> sharpens C1 (centralize-first); T3.2 stays xl, T3.3 stays l. jj-era upgrade.rs must be REPLACED not extended. Ready for lead review."}	blake3:WgJ9SCrFMkGTFkQVYD2rYiQlv0wfqERpGoOM8FRvvgs
