1779062045586800	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyjxA		item.comment	bn-2sw3	{"body":"T3.1 (bn-tmt8) is your spec — see notes/sg3-layout-design.md. Sizing holds at xl (relocation, 0 engine rewrites — SP4 verdict) but internally re-weighted: the C1 root.join(\"ws\") sweep is ~84 sites across 27 FILES (SP4's '~12' was ~7x low; full file list in §4.2). NORMATIVE constraints: C1 land the centralization sweep as ONE greppable zero-behaviour commit BEFORE flipping workspaces_dir(); C3 any diff touching build/collect/merge/diff3 or refs/manifold/* LOGIC is out-of-scope and a review-blocker (relocation only); C5 exact order: C1 sweep -> flip helper+git_cwd+target-resolution+backend.list+ancestor-walk -> init drop set_bare_mode/clean_root_worktree -> migrate (T3.3) -> test-fixture sweep. C4: add path-based belt-and-braces guard in handle_post_merge_destroy."}	blake3:kX-MVxAjZbFMg-N12O-Hqn38dOqgcV0KkK6XVev2W4U
1779062045688842	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEykBA		item.comment	bn-3kkl	{"body":"T3.1 (bn-tmt8) fully specifies you — see notes/sg3-layout-design.md §7: a 14-step crash-safe 'maw migrate' algorithm (Phases A preflight/refuse-if-in-flight-merge, B preserve-everything via existing snapshot_working_copy+recovery refs, C relocate worktrees, D un-bare root + materialize branch [the #9 hard kernel], E finalize/verify). Build on EXISTING Prime-Invariant machinery (snapshot_working_copy, Step-0 ANCHOR, replay_snapshot_with_merge_protection, recovery-ref pinning) — do not reinvent. REPLACE the jj-era upgrade.rs, do NOT retrofit it (it's jj-based). Crash-safety via .manifold/migration/journal.json. Your AC maps 1:1 to Phase B (unconditional pre-snapshot) + Phase E step 14 (maw doctor clean + DST oracles pass + no recover-loss). Size l holds."}	blake3:mzq7AyJ3ZhVqS6V2b73QMWKN0ybtdATTgnpy8E3XXqE
1779062356455130	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEykRA		item.comment	bn-263u	{"body":"Implemented (committed 0560bc9, NOT merged): (1) production MAW_FP env bridge in maw-core failpoints.rs (parse_env_spec + KNOWN_FAILPOINTS glob table + OnceLock init_from_env, wired into maw-cli main; new maw-cli failpoints feature for the shipped faithful binary) gated behind --features failpoints, zero-overhead default; (2) harness fault layer crates/maw-assurance/src/fault.rs (fault-injection feature): FaultPlan::from_seed deterministic crash plan, InProcFault RAII registry control, SubprocFault real kill -9 -<pgid> + SP1 Finding B child-reaping + bounded self-healing recovery retry. Verified: cargo check --features failpoints PASS; cargo test -p maw-core --features failpoints failpoints 15/15 PASS (9 new parser tests); cargo check (no fp) PASS zero-overhead; maw-assurance fault tests 6/6 PASS; maw-cli --features failpoints binary builds; clippy clean. Pre-existing (not mine): clear_single_failpoint parallel-flake + fp_commit clippy-with-failpoints lints, both byte-identical on main. bn-32k3 unblocked. Notes: ws/bn-263u/notes/sg1-fault-injection-notes.md"}	blake3:ygTtwhIkBkv3LxXHoeYdsjsunv3SwfiGFCm_YlVvBAc
