1779062614790806	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEykxA		item.create	bn-2017	{"description":"Found by T1.5 (bn-263u), verified byte-identical on pristine main —\nPRE-EXISTING, not a bn-263u regression.\n\nOBJECTIVE\nThe failpoints REGISTRY is a process-global with no per-test isolation.\nThe maw-core test clear_single_failpoint passes serial but is flaky when\ncargo runs tests in parallel threads (shared global state, no mutex\npartitioning per test). This matters for SG1: the DST harness and the\nbounded per-commit CI (T1.7 bn-1gp4) run failpoint-bearing tests, and a\nflaky registry test undermines the trust instrument's own green signal.\n\nAPPROACH\nOptions to evaluate: (a) #[serial] gate the registry-mutating tests\n(serial_test crate or a shared test mutex); (b) make the REGISTRY\nthread-local for the test cfg; (c) snapshot/restore REGISTRY around each\ntest via an RAII guard. Pick the one that keeps production set()/check()\nunchanged (zero-overhead default contract).\n\nACCEPTANCE CRITERIA\n- cargo test -p maw-core --features failpoints passes reliably under the\n  default parallel test runner (repeat 10x, 0 flakes).\n- No change to production set()/check()/clear* behaviour or the\n  zero-overhead non-failpoints build.\n\nCONTEXT POINTERS\ncrates/maw-core/src/failpoints.rs (REGISTRY, clear_single_failpoint,\nclear_all) ; relates to bn-1gp4 (T1.7 CI) and bn-32k3 (T1.6\ndeterminism) ; flagged in notes/sg1-fault-injection-notes.md (bn-263u).\n","kind":"bug","labels":["dst","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-3nw1","size":"s","title":"failpoints REGISTRY: clear_single_failpoint flaky under parallel test threads"}	blake3:rxSSLnEQfBT3X8AuaoLbKwYfqlh8JHzA-TGbad2e_kc
1779062615038563	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEylBA		item.create	bn-2ors	{"description":"Found by T1.5 (bn-263u), verified PRE-EXISTING (bn-1cww's landed code,\nuntouched by bn-263u). Not a bn-263u regression.\n\nOBJECTIVE\n`clippy -p maw-cli --features failpoints` flags two lints in\nsrc/merge/commit.rs::fp_commit. bn-1cww deliberately dropped `const`\nfrom fp_commit so the --features failpoints body (fallible fp!()) would\ncompile; clippy's nursery `missing_const_for_fn` now fires on the\nno-feature shape. The default CI gate (`just clippy` =\n`cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -D warnings`, NO\n--features failpoints) is clean, so this is latent — BUT bn-kwm7's SG1\nCI design (notes/sg1-dst-architecture.md §7) specifies a dedicated\n`--features failpoints` faithful-binary build job. If that job runs\nclippy with the workspace nursery=deny lints, this becomes a hard CI\nfailure for SG1's own faithful tier.\n\nAPPROACH\nAdd a targeted `#[cfg_attr(not(feature = \"failpoints\"),\nallow(clippy::missing_const_for_fn))]` (or equivalent scoped allow with\na comment citing bn-1cww) on fp_commit so it is clean under BOTH feature\nconfigs without re-introducing the const-fn build-breaker. Confirm the\nsecond flagged lint and address it the same way.\n\nACCEPTANCE CRITERIA\n- `cargo clippy -p maw-cli --features failpoints --all-targets\n  -- -D warnings` is clean.\n- `just clippy` (default, no failpoints) remains clean.\n- `cargo build --features failpoints` still compiles (bn-1cww fix\n  intact — do NOT re-add `const`).\n\nCONTEXT POINTERS\nsrc/merge/commit.rs::fp_commit (the bn-1cww fix) ; bn-1cww (done) ;\nbn-1gp4 (T1.7 CI faithful-binary job) ; notes/sg1-dst-architecture.md §7\n; flagged in notes/sg1-fault-injection-notes.md (bn-263u).\n","kind":"bug","labels":["dst","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-3nw1","size":"xs","title":"clippy: missing_const_for_fn on fp_commit under maw-cli --features failpoints"}	blake3:_ZlpLTgtWxIYCMygP3BsxsxGpbwmoIbY5nlStW-dkzs
1779403093336825	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEylRA		item.comment	bn-2j45	{"body":"T2.7 (bn-2ftq) review pass 1 surfaced product/ergonomics suggestions that are SG4 input (not pre-reg material) — captured here for the audit trail per the T2.7 §12 Disposition commitment: (1) machine-readable workspace manifest; (2) maw status --json answering 'where am I/what other ws/what stale/what to integrate' in one call; (3) maw doctor + maw repair coverage expansion (moved root, deleted WT dir, stale git WT metadata, missing .maw state, interrupted command, duplicate branch, orphaned ws, concurrent maw lock, mismatched base ref); (4) append-only event log (workspace_created/agent_started/snapshot_recorded/integration_started/conflict_detected/integration_completed/workspace_cleaned/repair_performed) as recovery oracle and benchmark evidence; (5) maw crib <agent> CLI emitting per-agent protocol; (6) .mawinclude (env propagation, hooks); (7) safe-cleanup state vocabulary (clean/dirty-uncommitted/committed-unintegrated/integrated/abandoned-with-snapshot); (8) mergeback queue (maw integrate --queue/--next/--abort/--resume with provenance + overlap tracking); (9) first-class overkill-line CLI guidance ('use plain Claude/Codex worktrees for one-off independent tasks; use maw when N agents, overlapping files, or integration queue risk exceeds X'). The SG2 publication's overkill-regime commitment (T5.3 / §2 of T2.7) is the publication-side; #9 above is the product-side. See ws/bn-2ftq/notes/sg2-benchmark-preregistration.md §12 and the source review sg2-benchmark-preregistration.review.1.md."}	blake3:jKqNaGClngLgCkHPyPHcvHqhor-Ek8CFXKt0FkiKjEI
1779653108767551	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEylhA		item.move	bn-2ftq	{"state":"done"}	blake3:rQn0jzfCrDKXZViBtZZXbvgY371id-UydQvM4p0hGAw
1779719190047339	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEylxA		item.create	bn-2kgu	{"description":"OBJECTIVE\nGet a directional agent-ergonomics signal on the consolidated .maw/\nlayout BEFORE T3.2 commits to the xl implementation, so the worst\ncase shrinks from \"implement xl + revert xl\" to \"directional\nno-go, leave default unchanged, T3.2 ships as a configurable\nno-default-change feature.\" Output is a go/no-go memo for T3.2,\nNOT a rigorous benchmark and NOT a T3.5 surrogate.\n\nWHY THIS SPIKE EXISTS\nSP4 (bn-gh1p) proved the ENGINE can do the layout move.\nT3.1 (bn-tmt8) specified the new layout precisely. Neither asked\n\"do agents like it?\" The rigorous answer is T3.5 (bn-1uzn) — but\nT3.5 is downstream of the full SG2 benchmark machinery (T1.2 ->\nT2.1 -> T2.2 -> T2.6) and lands AFTER T3.2/T3.3 are implemented.\nIf T3.5 no-gos, we have already invested ~xl + l + m of mostly\nproduction code. SP5 is the cheap, early, DIRECTIONAL signal that\ngates the T3.2 xl commitment.\n\nAPPROACH\n1. Build a minimal prototype of the consolidated .maw/ layout in a\n   throwaway repo under /tmp — just enough for agents to run in:\n     - workspace-create writes to .maw/workspaces/<name>/\n     - .manifold/ redirected to .maw/manifold/ via a thin path\n       shim (a feature-flag-style entry point, NOT the full\n       ~84-site sweep T3.2 will do)\n     - .maw/.gitignore + a stub .maw/config.toml\n     - Add the `worktree` and `wt` clap aliases (the T3.4 scope\n       addition) so the prototype exercises the agent-facing\n       surface T3.4 will ship\n   Do NOT do: the full centralization sweep, init un-bare, or\n   migration. Those are T3.2 / T3.3 scope. Use a flag or shim.\n2. Run a small agent-ergonomics comparison using SP3's driver\n   pattern (`claude -p --output-format json`, scenario repos\n   under /tmp with no CLAUDE.md/AGENTS.md/.mcp.json — SP3 §2\n   auth gotcha applies):\n     - N ~ 3 / arm\n     - 2 tasks (one collision-light, one with overlap)\n     - 2 arms: current `ws/` layout vs prototype `.maw/workspaces/`\n       layout\n     - Honor SP3 §1 fairness controls (same scenario, same crib,\n       same seed per task)\n3. Look qualitatively for: gross regressions, agent confusion,\n   hidden-dir invisibility tripping `cd` / `ls` / `find` /\n   `git status` mental models, agents not discovering files,\n   AGENTS.md alone being insufficient as the path-handed-to-agent,\n   any unanticipated breakage in the workspace lifecycle.\n4. DELIVERABLE: ws/<spike-ws>/notes/sp5-layout-ergonomics-directional.md\n   with the directional verdict (proceed-with-T3.2 / proceed-with-\n   caveats / revisit-before-T3.2) and named risks if any.\n\nACCEPTANCE CRITERIA\n- Prototype lifecycle runs end-to-end on the throwaway repo:\n  create -> edit -> commit -> merge -> destroy on the\n  .maw/workspaces/ layout.\n- Comparison run with N >= 3 / arm on >= 2 tasks on real (not\n  mocked) agent runs; cost + transcripts captured per run.\n- Memo includes a clear DIRECTIONAL verdict for T3.2, with named\n  risks the T3.2 design should mitigate.\n- Memo explicitly states: this is NOT a numeric benchmark, NOT a\n  T3.5 surrogate, NOT a source of pre-registered bars. Pilot-rule\n  discipline per T2.7 §3.1 applies: SP5 data is excluded from\n  SG2/SG3/SG4 analysis and the publication. (This is what makes\n  the spike LEGAL under the T2.7 freeze.)\n- Bone left in `doing` for lead review/merge — do NOT close, do\n  NOT merge to default, do NOT push.\n\nCONTEXT POINTERS\n- ws/default/notes/sg3-layout-design.md (T3.1, bn-tmt8) — the\n  target spec. NOTE the directory-naming override: per the\n  2026-05-25 terminology decision, use `.maw/workspaces/` NOT\n  `.maw/worktrees/` (workspaces stays as on-disk + canonical\n  command name; `worktree`/`wt` are command aliases only).\n- ws/default/notes/layout-engine-impact.md (SP4, bn-gh1p) —\n  engine-impact assessment, the 13 assumptions, the privileged-\n  root-update reuse pattern.\n- ws/default/notes/agent-benchmark-feasibility.md (SP3, bn-2ixm)\n  — driver pattern (`claude -p --output-format json`), the auth\n  gotcha (--bare breaks OAuth), scenario isolation under /tmp.\n- ws/default/notes/sg2-benchmark-preregistration.md (T2.7,\n  bn-2ftq) — §3.1 Pilot rule (the rule that makes this spike\n  legal: harness-validation pilots permitted, MUST NOT set bars,\n  MUST be excluded from publication).\n- Consolidated `.maw/` default layout (2026-05-25 decision):\n    .maw/.gitignore           tracks config.toml, ignores runtime\n    .maw/config.toml          bootstrap config (location fixed)\n    .maw/manifold/...         <- moved from <root>/.manifold/\n    .maw/workspaces/<name>/   <- moved from <root>/ws/<name>/\n    .maw/cache/               reserved (no top-level dirs later)\n  refs/manifold/* git refs stay put (do NOT migrate for v1.0).\n- The SP5 spike's output gates the START of T3.2 (bn-2sw3).\n  Negative directional signal => T3.2 ships as configurability\n  with the OLD default still being `ws/` (config-knob present,\n  no on-disk move); T3.5 measures both later. Positive signal =>\n  T3.2 ships with the consolidated `.maw/` default and\n  `maw migrate` (T3.3) becomes the recommended path.\n\nDEPENDS ON: bn-tmt8 (done), bn-2ixm (done).\nBLOCKS: bn-2sw3 (T3.2). Wire after creation.\n","kind":"task","labels":["layout","spike","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-2yh1","size":"m","title":"SP5 (spike) Layout-ergonomics directional gate before T3.2"}	blake3:pquF-L7Zi2ZDyqVdezl3AFEPdH1n8Vzwv8TBltbqpQM
1779719196577915	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEymBA		item.link	bn-2sw3	{"link_type":"blocks","target":"bn-2kgu"}	blake3:4aamUnH1QKpOhVRzGmK8Xnw6lB4EmuhfRFTG561qZYc
1779719249332807	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEymRA		item.comment	bn-2sw3	{"body":"T3.2 RESHAPE per 2026-05-25 v1.0 layout-design decisions (supersedes T3.1 directory-naming, broadens centralization scope; T3.1 sections 1-7 semantics otherwise stand). (1) Implement MawLayout config struct in maw-core/config with every layout path overridable + sensible defaults documented; access layer reads from struct, not hardcoded constants. (2) Consolidated .maw/ namespace = single maw-owned subtree: .maw/.gitignore (tracks config.toml, ignores runtime subtrees), .maw/config.toml (bootstrap, fixed location), .maw/manifold/ (moved from repo-root/.manifold/), .maw/workspaces/[name]/ (moved from repo-root/ws/[name]/ — NOTE workspaces stays as on-disk dir name + canonical 'maw ws' command per terminology decision; T3.4 ships worktree/wt as command aliases), .maw/cache/ (reserved). (3) EXTEND T3.1 C1 to BOTH helpers: workspaces_dir() AND new manifold_dir(); centralize ALL repo-root/ws AND ALL repo-root/.manifold sites onto helpers as ONE greppable zero-behaviour commit BEFORE flipping defaults. C3 (no engine/refs logic diffs) and C5 sequencing (centralize, then flip helper, then init drops, then migrate, then fixtures) still apply. (4) refs/manifold/ git refs STAY PUT — do NOT migrate ref names for v1.0 (recovery refs too delicate; manifold-as-schema-name coexists fine with maw-as-tool-name). (5) NEW BLOCKER bn-2kgu (SP5 directional ergonomics spike): T3.2 should NOT start until SP5 returns directional go. Negative signal means T3.2 ships as pure-configurability with OLD default still ws/; positive signal means T3.2 ships consolidated .maw/ default + T3.3 maw migrate as recommended path. (6) Reversibility: every path is a config knob + C1/C1' centralization lands as separate zero-behaviour commit, so worst-case undo after a T3.5 no-go shrinks from 'rip out xl of production code' to 'leave config defaults at ws/'. xl sizing holds. Authoritative spec for engine seams + migration algorithm: ws/default/notes/sg3-layout-design.md (with the directory-naming + scope overrides above)."}	blake3:7bKpm9EPEvoV6vh9m6Cq24jMkfeIWHdVbXvnekcbJlE
1779719254854838	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEymhA		item.comment	bn-1jqo	{"body":"T3.4 SCOPE ADDITION per 2026-05-25 terminology decision: include 'worktree' and 'wt' clap aliases for the 'maw ws' subcommand group (so 'maw worktree create alice' and 'maw wt create alice' both route to the same code as 'maw ws create alice'). Implementation is clap-native — one alias annotation per subcommand. Rationale: workspaces stays canonical in commands, docs, and on-disk paths (per the 2026-05-25 decision to keep workspace terminology); the alias gives agents who reach for the git-fluent name from muscle memory a working command instead of an error, AND serves as a future-switch escape hatch (if canonical ever flips, the alias has already been the public path so it isn't a real breaking change). T3.4 scope grows by +xs (alias annotations only); size stays m. Docs lead with workspaces; mention aliases in --help and AGENTS.md. SP5 bn-2kgu prototype includes these aliases so the agent-facing surface T3.4 ships is exercised in the directional eval."}	blake3:7gkp5aWs32q9jGXqjB_62QqCOi9pAIeRP3D4XkQ7sWw
