1779729588068435	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyvxA		item.comment	bn-6308	{"body":"Pilot GREEN: 0/64032 op-steps (Wilson 95% UB 5.999e-5). Calibration finding: actual throughput ~46 op-steps/sec single-thread, ~17x slower than arch doc — reframed target as two-tier (1e8 v1.0 floor / 1e9 stretch). Recipe just sg1-soak-pilot wired; per-commit corpus + cargo check green. Doc: notes/sg1-soak-campaign.md. SG1 (bn-3nw1) closable: artifact + harness + pilot deliverables met; 1e8 floor is cron-calendar follow-on."}	blake3:hxBQFifZUQdWi5TAN0goyr6Goc6Xrjb62gki_cNVImI
1779729800706824	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEywBA		item.create	bn-2yzz	{"description":"Open a new tracking bone (per lead decision on 2026-05-25) for the\ncron-driven accumulation toward the SG1 v1.0 release-gate floor of\n>= 1e8 fault-injected op-steps at ConditionProfile::default() in the\nsg1_nightly_soak test, with 0 Oracle A/B violations.\n\nContext\n-------\nbn-3nw1 (SG1 instrument) auto-closed when its last child bn-6308 (T1.9)\nclosed. The T1.9 follow-up reframed the published target into two\ntiers (notes/sg1-soak-campaign.md §1.1) after the pilot revealed the\narchitecture's 42 ms/seed throughput prediction overstated reality by\n~17x (actual: ~46 op-steps/sec single-threaded):\n\n- v1.0 release-gate FLOOR: >= 1e8 op-steps (Wilson 95% UB 3.84e-8)\n- Asymptotic STRETCH:      >= 1e9 op-steps (Wilson 95% UB 3.84e-9)\n\nThe 1e8 floor is the concrete v1.0 dependency. The instrument is done;\nthis bone tracks the calendar-driven evidence accumulation that turns\nthe §7.1 publication-row template into populated headline numbers.\n\nAcceptance criteria\n-------------------\n1. Cumulative clean in-proc op-steps in the sg1_nightly_soak cron\n   (.github/workflows/dst-soak.yml) crosses 1e8 with 0 Oracle A/B\n   violations observed.\n2. notes/sg1-soak-campaign.md §7.1 (v1.0-floor publication-row\n   template) is filled in with: final N, Wilson 95% CI, seed-range\n   manifest, harness commit SHA at campaign close, faithful-slot\n   count.\n3. The §8 slot ledger has the per-slot rows that compose the\n   cumulative N (append-only; SHA-bump rules per §2 stop condition 3\n   apply if oracle/generator/failpoint surface changes mid-campaign).\n4. Any oracle violation during accrual is treated per §2 stop\n   condition 2: shrink (T1.6) -> corpus-promote (T1.8) -> fix ->\n   restart from step 0 on a fresh base seed; counter resets per the\n   published discipline.\n\nCalendar estimate\n-----------------\nAt single-threaded cron throughput (~46 op-steps/sec) and default\nslot budget (SG1_NIGHTLY_SEEDS=100000, SG1_NIGHTLY_STEPS=64):\n~25 nightly slots ~= 25 nights of cron from the harness commit SHA in\n§4 of the soak doc. A tuned workflow_dispatch slot\n(SG1_NIGHTLY_SEEDS=1_000_000) compresses materially; out of scope\nhere unless calendar slips.\n\nNon-goals\n---------\n- Profile-spectrum sweep (deferred per soak doc §9).\n- Cross-machine bit-exactness audit (deferred per §9).\n- 1e9 stretch (separate follow-on; not v1.0-gating).\n- Faithful-tier in the in-proc counter (reported as separate slot\n  count per soak doc §1.3).\n\nPredecessors\n------------\n- bn-3nw1 (SG1 instrument — done)\n- bn-6308 (T1.9 published artifact + harness — done)\n","kind":"task","labels":["dst","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"l","title":"SG1 1e8 op-step cron accrual — v1.0 release-gate evidence row"}	blake3:jjwIAeB4pZZT6YgHssKjy5BaIc6StoULDmb-r6Atyx4
1779730134767589	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEywRA		item.create	bn-iux4	{"description":"SG3 (bn-2yh1) is gated verbatim on \"a pre-registered ergonomics eval\n(subset of SG2) showing no agent regression vs the current layout\".\nToday the SUBSET and the meaning of \"no regression\" are not pinned;\nthis bone freezes them BEFORE any layout work begins, so the gate\nhas teeth (and so SG3 cannot be merged with a softened bar).\n\nPre-condition: this bone runs AFTER SG2 (bn-2jwi) has produced its\nbaseline benchmark on the current ws/ layout. Without that baseline\nthere is no \"before\" to compare a layout change against.\n\nAcceptance criteria\n-------------------\n1. notes/sg3-subset-prereg.md (new doc) committed under default,\n   frozen BEFORE any SG3 implementation commit lands.\n\n2. The doc specifies, by name and seed range:\n   a. Which subset of SG2's pre-registered seeds is the layout-eval\n      subset (smaller N than full SG2; rationale on why this N gives\n      adequate power to detect a regression at the chosen MDE).\n   b. Which exact metrics carry forward from T2.4 (non-composited):\n      tool-calls, turns-to-done, work-lost events, work-redone /\n      wasted-turns, human interventions, and any maw-specific\n      per-verb attribution from T2.5.\n   c. Which substrates are evaluated (maw at old layout vs maw at\n      new layout — substrate adapters from T2.3 must support both;\n      worktrees+convention and jj are NOT in the subset because the\n      gate is about maw-vs-maw, not maw-vs-rivals).\n\n3. The doc specifies, quantitatively, what \"no regression\" means:\n   a. For each metric, the regression rule (e.g., new-layout median\n      within X% of old-layout median, OR new-layout Wilson-CI for\n      zero-event metrics does not move the upper bound by more than\n      a stated margin).\n   b. The dominance-axis rule (the SG2 crossover point cannot shift\n      adversely by more than a stated margin in the hostile\n      direction).\n   c. The minimum-detectable-effect (MDE) the chosen subset N\n      actually has power for, computed from the SP3 statistical\n      framework borrowed in T2.7 §6.\n   d. The pre-registered direction: this is a SUPERIORITY-or-EQUIVALENCE\n      test biased against the layout change (the burden is on the\n      layout change to demonstrate non-inferiority; ties go to the\n      old layout).\n\n4. The doc states the FAILURE MODE explicitly: if the new-layout\n   subset re-run shows regression beyond the pre-registered bar,\n   SG3 does NOT ship in v1.0 and is rolled to v1.1; v1.0 launches on\n   the current ws/ layout (matching the original bn-2yh1 framing of\n   \"must NOT block the trust artifact\").\n\n5. The doc is gated into CI: a CHECK that adds a comment of the\n   form \"SG3 subset pre-reg: notes/sg3-subset-prereg.md exists and\n   is older than any modification to crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/\n   create.rs\". (Implementation light: a small `just sg3-prereg-check`\n   recipe that does the date comparison; CI invokes it.)\n\nNon-goals\n---------\n- The actual subset RUN (that's the SG3-implementation re-run on\n  the new layout; this bone produces only the rule, not the result).\n- A reframe of SG2 (this bone consumes SG2's pre-reg surface as-is\n  via T2.7 / bn-2ftq).\n- Any layout-implementation work (separate SG3 children).\n\nWhy size=s\n----------\nThis is a documentation + tiny CI check, not the eval itself. The\neval is SG3's existing layout-change-children that will reference\nthis doc for their acceptance criterion.\n\nPredecessors\n------------\n- SG2 baseline (bn-2jwi) must produce the comparison baseline first.\n- T2.7 (bn-2ftq, done) — borrows the pre-reg discipline.\n","kind":"task","labels":["layout","benchmark","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-2yh1","size":"s","title":"SG3 layout-change ergonomics subset — pre-register subset + regression criterion BEFORE the layout work"}	blake3:0Afjiro-ljihLlZ6b-WaU62RqAUye6Kv3xnXJ-wAR_I
