1777920885823725	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy6ww		item.create	bn-284w	{"description":"Manual break-test in /tmp/maw-branch-target.xRkU4B found that after merging worker work into a branch-attached workspace (`crib2` attached to `crib-graph`), `maw ws list --format text` renders `crib2` as `(ready to merge)` and prints `Merge ready: maw ws merge crib2 --into default --destroy`. The same happens for change primary workspaces such as `ch-amb` attached to `feat/ch-amb-flow`.\n\nWhy this is bad: these workspaces are long-lived branch/PR targets. Listing them as ready to merge into default encourages accidentally pulling branch-only or change-only work into trunk.\n\nExpected: branch-attached/change-target workspaces should display their attached branch and branch-local ahead state, but should not be included in default-target merge-ready advice. Suggested guidance should point at creating/merging worker work into the attached workspace/branch, or omit merge-ready advice for target workspaces entirely.","kind":"bug","labels":["merge","workspace","status"],"size":"m","title":"ws list suggests merging branch targets into default"}	blake3:xFSZH4junyfJGTfvcs3xJsRZk8v0dRUiI6430Ieh2MY
1777920894872491	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy7Aw		item.create	bn-6ccl	{"description":"Manual break-test in /tmp/maw-branch-target.xRkU4B created a plain directory `ws/not-a-worktree` and then ran `maw ws attach-branch not-a-worktree crib-graph`. The command succeeded and wrote metadata even though the directory is not a tracked git worktree/workspace.\n\nFollow-up merge (`maw ws merge fake-worker --into not-a-worktree --message ...`) failed later with: `failed to inspect target workspace 'not-a-worktree': ... does not appear to be a git repository`. `maw ws list` also does not list the fake target because the backend does not know about it.\n\nExpected: `maw ws attach-branch` should validate that the target is an existing tracked workspace via the backend, not merely that `ws/<name>` exists as a directory. It should fail early with a clear `workspace is not tracked; create or attach the workspace first` style message and should not write metadata for arbitrary directories.","kind":"bug","labels":["workspace","merge"],"size":"s","title":"ws attach-branch accepts directories that are not workspaces"}	blake3:z2aeJBiIKQKcYOoIzFXB01_5Jw3XvHd1ZVTWBkVbhSE
