1778368908387341	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEypg0		item.comment	bn-3r8s	{"body":"Reproduced on current main (commit 0f6ab49 + bn-2upt branch).\n\nSetup:\n1. Add 9413-line Rust file with 100 nearly-identical impl SynthHandler blocks on main.\n2. Create workspace, edit Synth050's warmup (4-line addition), commit.\n3. Edit Synth075's warmup (3-line addition) directly on default, commit.\n4. `maw epoch sync` (epoch -> branch).\n5. `maw ws sync <ws>` -> rebases workspace onto new epoch, reports clean.\n6. `maw ws merge <ws> --into default --destroy` -> reports success, no warnings.\n\nOutcome:\n- COMMIT tree at HEAD: 9420 lines, NO conflict markers, both edits applied correctly. The merge engine produced the right answer.\n- WORKTREE on disk: 18,840 lines (exactly 2x), with diff3 markers wrapping the file. `<<<<<<< bn-X (merged workspace)` at line 1, `||||||| base` at 9422 (empty base section), `=======` at 9423, `>>>>>>> default (local edits)` at 18840. Both halves are full copies of the 9420-line tree with each edit in its expected position.\n\nThis is the silent-corruption shape that matches the bn-4c6g report. The agent runs `cargo build` against the corrupted worktree, sees garbage, has no signal that the COMMIT itself is fine.\n\nSuspected root cause: the merge `update_default_workspace` -> `replay_snapshot_with_merge_protection` path (crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/merge.rs:4750). Default's snapshot from PREPARE included its committed-but-not-epoch-synced delta on synth_handlers.rs. After the merge tree was checked out (correct content), the snapshot replay applied default's delta on top, generating an Add/Add conflict against the merge result — committed as markers in the worktree but not in the tree.\n\nThe 'direct commit on default + epoch sync' shape was the trigger here. Same shape that bn-28q2 fixed for FF-absorb. Likely the same class of bug: maw epoch sync doesn't advance default's snapshot baseline, so subsequent merge thinks default has uncommitted local edits when it doesn't.\n\nReproduction artifact left in /home/bob/src/maw/ws/default/synth_handlers.rs and the bn-3r8s-test workspace is destroyed (snapshot saved)."}	blake3:FYtQWXSojVjswedf7ACPrC2NpX32QRvfYdOYCaN-2sM
