1778439961839379	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyqw0		item.create	bn-qw4i	{"description":"Problem\n-------\n`maw ws merge <ws> --into default --check` reports \"[OK] Ready to merge\" for a workspace with unresolved structured conflicts. The actual merge then refuses with a conflict error. `--check` is supposed to be a dry-run preview; it should fail with the same diagnostic when a real merge would fail.\n\nReproduction (stress test, 2026-05-10)\n--------------------------------------\n1. Create two workspaces from main, both edit the same line in the same file, commit.\n2. Merge the first (advances epoch).\n3. Auto-rebase rebases the second with a conflict (\"rebased with N conflicts\").\n4. `maw ws merge <second> --into default --check` → \"Ready to merge\".\n5. `maw ws merge <second> --into default --destroy` → refuses with conflict error.\n\nFiles\n-----\n- `crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/merge.rs` — `--check` path missing the same conflict-marker / sidecar gate the real precondition fires.\n\nSize\n----\nS — wire the precondition into check path; add an integration test pairing `--check` against a known-conflicted workspace.","kind":"bug","labels":["correctness","ux","merge"],"size":"s","title":"maw ws merge --check accepts workspace with unresolved conflicts that merge then refuses"}	blake3:dhjFckYi5b1lb5TBaElMmCsB-Rm8ksP2kt4Rs0h-atU
1778439988797459	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyrA0		item.create	bn-3fhj	{"description":"Problem\n-------\nIf the user (or a misbehaving tool) deletes a workspace's worktree directory under `ws/<name>/`, maw's metadata under `.manifold/` is still present. `maw ws list` and `maw status` continue to list the workspace and report \"Merge ready: maw ws merge <name> --into default --destroy\". The actual `maw ws merge` then fails:\n\n  Error: Workspace 'kill-test' does not exist at /tmp/maw-stress/ws/kill-test\n    Check available workspaces: maw ws list\n\nThe error even points back to `ws list` — which is the source of the wrong information.\n\nReproduction (stress test, 2026-05-10)\n--------------------------------------\n1. `maw ws create kill-test --from main`.\n2. Delete `ws/kill-test/` from disk (simulating crash or rogue cleanup).\n3. `maw ws list` → still shows kill-test as ready to merge.\n4. `maw ws merge kill-test --into default --destroy` → \"does not exist\" error.\n\nGoal\n----\n`maw ws list` should detect missing worktrees and surface them as a distinct state (e.g. \"MISSING\") so the user can run `maw ws destroy <name> --force` to clean up the metadata. Same check should also fire in `maw ws merge --check`.\n\nFiles\n-----\n- `crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/list.rs` — add a worktree-existence check per row.\n- `crates/maw-core/src/backend/...` — verify the backend's `exists()` check considers actual disk state, or document that the registry can diverge from disk.\n\nSize\n----\nS — surface check in list; refuse merge with same error if check would fail.","kind":"bug","labels":["correctness","ux","workspace"],"size":"s","title":"maw ws list shows workspace as ready to merge after worktree directory is deleted"}	blake3:w4OIGZZ89tzy9UCDgmABZSACsbfsE0XAkLoLCzFbJ54
1778439989029504	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyrQ0		item.create	bn-17km	{"description":"Problem\n-------\n`maw ws merge <ws> --into default --destroy --message \"\"` accepts the empty string and produces a commit with literally no subject or body:\n\n  commit 58ac3b71d69431f1e4db268dcfbb9edd0690d908\n  Author: Test User <test@example.com>\n  Commit: Test User <test@example.com>\n  (no subject, no body)\n\nThe user-facing output also shows the artifact: `Merged to main:  from selftest` (double-space where the subject would be).\n\nBy contrast, omitting `--message` correctly refuses with a helpful message (\"No --message provided and stdin is not a terminal.\"). The validation should treat empty-string the same as missing.\n\nReproduction (stress test, 2026-05-10)\n--------------------------------------\n1. Create a workspace, commit a change in it.\n2. `maw ws merge <ws> --into default --destroy --message \"\"`.\n3. Inspect the resulting commit — no subject, no body.\n\nFiles\n-----\n- `crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/mod.rs` (clap definition for `--message`) — add a `value_parser` that rejects empty strings, or add an inline check in the merge handler.\n\nSize\n----\nS — one-line validation + a test.","kind":"bug","labels":["correctness","ux","merge"],"size":"s","title":"maw ws merge accepts empty --message and creates commit with no subject or body"}	blake3:HPpQ2AY3uMLsq1tKEdt3uhRO4PTwQQE968M-EuN19rk
