1778446489079163	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEytw0		item.create	bn-6q05	{"description":"The dst_action_sequences_preserve_contracts test in tests/action_workflow_dst.rs deterministically creates a state where an active change id and a workspace share the same name (e.g. 'ch-act-0'), then issues 'maw ws merge change-worker-N --into ch-act-0 --destroy' which correctly errors:\n\n  Error: Ambiguous merge target 'ch-act-0':\n    - active change id ch-act-0\n    - workspace ch-act-0\n  Use --into change:ch-act-0 or --into ws:ch-act-0.\n\nThe error is correct production behavior (introduced with branch-attached workspace targets), but the simulator was authored before this disambiguation existed and uses bare names. Failure surfaces with seed BASE_SEED+i for i in 0..8.\n\nFix options (test-side, preferred):\n- Update the simulator merge action to use 'change:<id>' or 'ws:<id>' explicit prefix when a name is known to collide.\n- Or have the simulator avoid creating workspace names that match active change ids.\n\nFiles\n-----\n- tests/action_workflow_dst.rs (or whichever helper it calls for the merge step)\n- tests/manifold_common/mod.rs:686 (the panic site)\n\nVerified preexisting on main before bn-qw4i/bn-3fhj/bn-17km work landed (2026-05-10).","kind":"bug","size":"s","title":"DST action_workflow: --into <name> ambiguity not handled when change-id and workspace collide"}	blake3:tFEOVp_qN5iphvtWPtXWFeOEHnGqMmAEWvVmvCWRLW0
