1778531353097620	crib-dev	itc:v3:AWKSTPJJJznM_QAAAAAAQareqru7fgAAAAEvAQ		item.create	bn-3bl2	{"description":"## Report\n\nHit the same symptom as **bn-129d** (which is marked done) in a fresh session. `maw ws merge` reports success and creates a merge commit, but the workspace's deletions are not applied to the target tree.\n\n## Reproduction (observed 2026-05-11 in the crib project)\n\nSequence that triggered it:\n1. Worker A merged into target `crib2`, deleting files `internal/temporal/activities/{artifacts,docker,docker_test,provenance_emit_test}.go` and `internal/temporal/workflow/{pipeline,step_executor}.go`. Merge succeeded; files were deleted on target.\n2. Workers B and C had stale copies of those files in their workspaces (their workspace base predated worker A's merge). They did not intentionally modify them.\n3. Merging B and C into `crib2` produced modify/delete conflicts on those files. Resolved with `--resolve-all=<worker-name>` (took worker side), which **re-introduced** the files on `crib2`.\n4. Created a fresh cleanup workspace from `crib2`. Ran `maw exec <ws> -- git rm <files>` then `maw exec <ws> -- git commit -m \"...\"`. The commit shows `delete mode 100644` for each file (2 files changed, 171 deletions(-)). `maw exec <ws> -- git ls-tree HEAD <dir>` confirms the files are gone in the workspace's HEAD tree. The workspace filesystem also confirms they are gone.\n5. `maw ws merge <ws> --into crib2 --destroy`. Output: `Merged to crib-graph: <message> from <ws>`. No conflicts reported.\n6. **Result**: the deleted files survive on `crib2`. `git ls-files crib/internal/temporal/activities/` still lists them. `git show HEAD --stat` shows zero file changes for the merge commit.\n\nReproduced **three times** in a row with three different cleanup workspaces (`cleanup-temporal-tests`, `cleanup-temporal-v2`, `cleanup-final`). Each produced an empty merge commit on the target.\n\n## Workaround\n\nDirect `maw exec crib2 -- git rm <files>` + `maw exec crib2 -- git commit` against the target branch works correctly. This bypasses the merge engine entirely.\n\n## Hypothesis\n\nThe deletion-snapshot path described in bn-129d analysis (`backend.snapshot()` diffing `git diff --name-status <current_epoch>` against working tree) likely doesn't see the deletion when:\n- The workspace's base epoch already had the files\n- The target (`<into>`) re-acquired the files between workspace creation and merge attempt (via modify/delete conflict resolution to the 'modify' side)\n- The workspace then deletes them and tries to merge again\n\nSo the snapshot diff between workspace and its base epoch is 'no change for those paths' (they're not in either), but the merge into target should still apply the deletion. Possibly the merge engine compares workspace tree against base epoch (not against target HEAD), so when both base epoch and workspace agree (file absent), no change is propagated even though target HEAD diverged.\n\n## Files to investigate (per bn-129d's analysis, may still apply)\n\n- src/backend/git.rs — snapshot() implementation\n- src/merge/collect.rs — phantom-deletion filter\n- src/merge/build.rs — tree deletion application\n\n## Related\n\n- bn-129d (done) — original report of this symptom. Either incomplete fix or a different code path.\n- bn-2pry (done) — '--keep both' on modify/delete silently inlines base. Adjacent symptom, different trigger.\n- bn-41c3 (done) — 'Prevent default workspace phantom deletions after mixed-target merges'. Adjacent.\n\n## Suggested regression test\n\n1. Init repo with files A, B.\n2. Create workspace w1 from main. Add file C. Merge w1 → main. main now has A, B, C.\n3. Create workspace w2 from main (so w2 base has A, B, C). w2 modifies A.\n4. In parallel, create workspace w3 from earlier main (base = A, B only, no C). w3 deletes B.\n5. Merge w3 → main. main now has A, C (B deleted).\n6. Merge w2 → main with --resolve-all=w2 (or similar conflict choice that re-introduces B if there's a conflict).\n7. Create workspace w4 from current main. 'git rm B'. Commit.\n8. Merge w4 → main.\n9. Assert: B is absent from main HEAD tree.\n\nStep 9 is what fails today.","kind":"bug","labels":["maw","merge","regression","deletions"],"size":"m","title":"regression: merge silently drops pure-deletion commits (recurrence of bn-129d)"}	blake3:D69BJSa2Il8nJdqLJ3o3CwC566znv-W83oDlmhFbP-k
