1778867457144571	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy4Q0		item.create	bn-oas3	{"description":"init.rs bf_get_dirty_files filters with !matches!(e.status, FileStatus::Untracked) to drop untracked files (legacy: exclude ?? lines from git status --porcelain). But status_head_to_worktree()/convert_status_item map untracked files to FileStatus::Added (gix Summary::Added), never FileStatus::Untracked — so the filter is dead and untracked files leak into dirty_files_at_root. Because brownfield step 2b renames .git->repo.git BEFORE step 4's bf_get_dirty_files, the entire renamed repo.git/ git-dir is walked as untracked->Added and reported as dirty, then moved into ws/default/. Test brownfield_moves_dirty_tracked_files_into_default FAILS on main (suite is red). Fix: exclude the list_untracked() set from the dirty list to faithfully reproduce 'porcelain minus ??'.","kind":"task","labels":["gix","fresh-eyes"],"title":"fix(gix): bf_get_dirty_files untracked filter is dead (status maps untracked->Added)"}	blake3:s4OweTPbO5fZ5wF1VfZEOhcXKH3CLeApqT7WoE5XF3k
