1778868731496793	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy5g0		item.create	bn-1tl6	{"description":"SEVERITY: HIGH — silent corruption of COMMITTED work in the merge commit (Prime-Invariant violation), plus the common-case loss of the executable bit on any merged script/binary.\n\nREPRO (deterministic, no conflict needed):\n  maw ws create w --from main\n  cd ws/w\n  printf '#!/bin/sh\\necho hi\\n' > tool.sh && chmod +x tool.sh   # mode 100755\n  ln -s tool.sh alias.sh                                        # mode 120000\n  git add -A && git commit -m x\n  # workspace tree:  tool.sh=100755, alias.sh=120000\n  cd ../.. && maw ws merge w --into default --destroy --message m\n  git -C ws/default ls-tree -r HEAD -- tool.sh alias.sh\n  # ACTUAL:   tool.sh=100644, alias.sh=100644   (blob OIDs identical)\n  # EXPECTED: tool.sh=100755, alias.sh=120000\n\nCONSEQUENCES:\n- Executable bit lost on every merged/new script or binary (high frequency, silent; git status clean because the wrong mode is baked into the merge commit).\n- symlink->file / file->symlink changes corrupt content: a regular file committed by an agent becomes a (often dangling) symlink in history whose target is the file's bytes; a symlink becomes a regular file containing the link-target text. Agent committed work is effectively destroyed in the merge commit. Confirmed both directions with dave/eve/gus scenarios.\n\nROOT CAUSE:\n- src/merge/collect.rs captures blob CONTENT only (read_committed_blob via HEAD:<path>, read_workspace_file via std::fs::read, git_hash_object). No EntryMode is ever recorded for the source workspace's path.\n- So FileChange.mode is None on the git worktree-backend merge path. crates/maw-core/src/merge/apply.rs:274 only sets entry.mode when change.mode.is_some(); otherwise it keeps the BASE epoch tree's mode for modified paths, and apply.rs:584 defaults new paths to EntryMode::Blob (100644).\n- diff_extract.rs/materialize.rs/apply.rs DO model modes (with unit tests), so the gap is specifically the production collect path not populating FileChange.mode from the workspace (HEAD tree entry mode for committed changes; symlink_metadata()/exec bit for worktree changes — same logic worktree_state_commit already uses correctly).\n\nSCOPE: merge collect/build path only. The recovery-snapshot path (worktree_state_commit + checkout_tree) preserves modes correctly — verified destroy --force + recover round-trips a symlink + exec bit intact. So this is NOT a general maw-git limitation; it is the merge engine discarding mode.\n\nNOT a v0.60.9-window regression (collect.rs content-only collection predates it; only test changes since v0.60.9) — but a real, serious, long-standing correctness bug surfaced by adversarial concurrent-agent testing.\n\nFIX DIRECTION: capture per-path EntryMode in collect.rs (read HEAD tree entry mode for committed files; symlink_metadata/exec for worktree files), thread it into FileChange.mode, and ensure apply.rs/build.rs use it for both modified and added paths (including patch_candidate_tree which also hardcodes EntryMode::Blob for conflict-resolved paths).","kind":"task","labels":["merge","prime-invariant","fresh-eyes"],"title":"fix(merge): merge engine drops file modes (exec bit + symlink) — corrupts committed history (Prime Invariant)"}	blake3:y_kUAt0ylqj_Swz6InglQMCr9xd_zHap1RXZBv3DqPA
1778868884960433	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy5w0		item.comment	bn-1tl6	{"body":"Refined scope from adversarial testing:\n\nAFFECTED (mode lost/corrupted in committed merge tree):\n- NEW path added by a workspace that is executable or a symlink -> becomes 100644 (apply.rs:584 unwrap_or(Blob)). Repro: tool.sh(100755)+alias.sh(120000) -> both 100644.\n- Existing path whose MODE CHANGES vs base epoch: file->symlink, symlink->file, or first chmod +x. The base mode is reused, so content is reinterpreted under the wrong mode (regular file's bytes become a dangling symlink target in history, or a symlink's target text becomes file content). Confirmed both directions.\n\nNOT AFFECTED (works correctly):\n- Edit-only of an existing file whose mode is unchanged vs base epoch: the base epoch tree mode is reused, so an existing 100755 script edited by an agent stays 100755. Verified (deploy.sh edit kept 100755).\n- Recovery-snapshot path (worktree_state_commit + checkout_tree): modes fully preserved (verified destroy --force + recover round-trips +x and symlink intact).\n\nSo severity is high but the most common case (editing an existing tracked script) is safe; the bug bites NEW executables/symlinks and mode flips — still a silent Prime-Invariant corruption for those, baked into history."}	blake3:4c9_Cb6GX2GW_t188C1r_Go_Im3NesiJJ4xPs8O7VnI
