1778884619972827	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy6w0		item.create	bn-phv1	{"description":"objects_impl::write_tree builds a gix::objs::Tree from caller entries and calls write_object without sorting. gix Tree::write_to only debug_assert!s sortedness, so in release builds unsorted entries produce a non-canonical/corrupt tree object (wrong OID, git fsck failure). Production callers pre-sort today but the invariant is unenforced. Fix: sort entries inside write_tree using gix's canonical Entry::Ord so it is correct-by-construction for all callers. Found in post-v0.60.9 fresh-eyes review.","kind":"bug","title":"fix(gix): write_tree silently writes corrupt trees in release (unsorted entries)"}	blake3:WGXt1-ACV3QEopVNMklbtnntA2-kNq8gyovB2h8cOKs
