1778956786699429	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy-w0		item.create	bn-cm63	{"description":"## Summary\nRunning `maw ws destroy <ws> --force` while a `maw ws merge <ws>` of the SAME\nworkspace is in flight leaves a permanently dangling `refs/manifold/head/<ws>`\noplog-head ref (a blob ref) with no owning workspace. 100% reproducible (6/6 in\nchaos testing). NOT a Prime-Invariant violation — the merged work still lands in\n`default` and a destroy recovery snapshot is created — but it is a real\nstate-hygiene defect.\n\n## Impact (severity: medium)\n- `maw doctor` perpetually emits `[WARN] stale head refs: found N head ref(s)\n  for non-existent workspaces`; they accumulate (one leaked ref per race).\n- Plain `maw gc` does NOT clean them (no head-ref cleanup performed); only the\n  more specific `maw gc --refs` does. doctor's hint does point to `gc --refs`,\n  but a user running plain `maw gc` will not clear the warning.\n- The orphaned ref is an oplog head (`refs/manifold/head/<ws>`, blob containing\n  `{\"workspace_id\":...,\"payload\":{\"type\":\"create\",...}}`) for a workspace that\n  no longer exists — risks confusing oplog/recovery tooling and unbounded ref\n  growth under repeated races (e.g. an orchestrator that destroys workspaces\n  while a batch merge is running).\n\n## Scope\n- ONLY the explicit destroy-vs-in-flight-merge race leaks: 6/6 reproductions.\n- Normal `maw ws merge <ws> --destroy` (the common agent path) is clean: 0/3.\n- Clean `maw ws destroy <ws>` of a non-merging workspace is clean (removes\n  refs/manifold/head/<ws> correctly; only the expected\n  refs/manifold/recovery/<ws>/... remains).\n\n## Reproduction (deterministic)\n1. In a maw repo, set a slow post-merge validation to widen the window:\n   `.manifold/config.toml`:\n     [merge.validation]\n     command = \"sleep 5\"\n2. `maw ws create rz --from main`; create+commit a file in ws/rz.\n3. `setsid maw ws merge rz --into default --message rz &`\n4. Poll `.manifold/merge-state.json` until `\"phase\": \"validate\"`.\n5. `maw ws destroy rz --force`   (succeeds, writes recovery snapshot)\n6. `wait` for the merge (it completes, work lands in default).\n7. `git -C <repo>.git for-each-ref | grep head/rz`  → `refs/manifold/head/rz`\n   STILL PRESENT (blob ref), workspace gone.\n8. `maw doctor` → `[WARN] stale head refs: found 1 ...`\n9. `maw gc` → does NOT clear it. `maw gc --refs` → clears it.\n\n## Likely root cause\n`maw ws destroy` deletes the workspace oplog head ref\n(`refs/manifold/head/<ws>`) during cleanup. The concurrently-running merge,\nhaving frozen the source workspace at PREPARE, continues through\nBUILD/VALIDATE/COMMIT/CLEANUP and appends an oplog operation for the source\nworkspace (the consume/merge op), which RE-CREATES `refs/manifold/head/<ws>`\nAFTER destroy already deleted it. There is no coordination (lock/serialization)\nbetween `maw ws destroy <ws>` and an in-flight `maw ws merge <ws>` on the same\nworkspace name, so the merge's oplog write resurrects a ref destroy meant to\nremove.\n\n## Suggested fixes (any one)\n- Have `maw ws destroy <ws>` detect an in-flight merge whose `sources` include\n  `<ws>` (merge-state.json) and refuse / serialize (mirror the\n  WorkspaceCreateLock pattern, bn-3bbc), OR\n- Have the merge oplog-append skip (or re-clean) the source workspace's\n  `refs/manifold/head/<ws>` when that workspace has been destroyed\n  (no worktree / destroy record present), OR\n- Make plain `maw gc` also prune dangling oplog head refs (refs/manifold/head/*\n  with no corresponding workspace), so the documented cleanup actually clears\n  the doctor warning.\n\n## Found by\nAdversarial chaos testing of the post-v0.60.9 gix-migration binary\n(/tmp/maw-chaos). All other scenarios (concurrent same/distinct creates,\ncreate/destroy churn, concurrent + stale + N-way merges, SIGKILL mid-VALIDATE +\nrecovery, gix symlink/exec-bit/tree-sort/binary/weird-name/type-flip handling,\ncorrupt merge-state) passed with the Prime Invariant intact and `git fsck`\nclean.","kind":"bug","title":"destroy racing an in-flight merge of the same workspace leaks a dangling refs/manifold/head/<ws> oplog ref"}	blake3:pjHHTtLueEWcnfr5_eZXTKBUKMD3GaXDZUHSohtPhBE
1778957789393882	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy_A0		item.move	bn-cm63	{"state":"doing"}	blake3:a5w8MVGGu8QXUoAk8XqrsC6rToAInOfM0-6mfBkG5pM
