1778965659770027	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEysA8		item.create	bn-120t	{"description":"OBJECTIVE\nConvert T2.8's prioritized friction list into concrete fix child-tasks\nunder SG4, highest measured agent-turn-cost first.\n\nACCEPTANCE CRITERIA\n- Child fix-tasks created and ordered by measured cost, each with a target\n  metric delta.\n\nDEPENDS ON: T2.8.\nCONTEXT POINTERS: T2.8 report.\n","kind":"task","labels":["v1-0","ergonomics"],"parent":"bn-2j45","size":"s","title":"T4.1 Triage SG2 diagnostic into a ranked fix backlog"}	blake3:Cm6wXAz7pzRVGcZK1tdUOpKrNlU1NeLsQn2TJoQzfOA
1778965660022428	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEysQ8		item.create	bn-350o	{"description":"OBJECTIVE\nUmbrella for the concrete fixes spawned by T4.1. Likely candidates from\nthis session: structured-conflict workspace UX, stale-workspace state\nlegibility (the \"behind the epoch\" messaging), the maw ws merge --abort /\nretry flow, and sharper self-describing output for scarce maw verbs.\n\nACCEPTANCE CRITERIA\n- Each child fix has a measured before/after wasted-turn delta from the\n  benchmark.\n\nDEPENDS ON: T4.1.\nCONTEXT POINTERS: chaos-session observations (structured conflict markers,\n\"stale\" workspace state, --abort recovery) ; memory: agent-fluency.\n","kind":"task","labels":["v1-0","ergonomics"],"parent":"bn-2j45","size":"l","title":"T4.2 Harden the highest-cost verbs/states"}	blake3:V2JyAujk8DiyCPiR3_DLyIkol0jXasllqAhkWqXAG3Y
1778965660290879	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEysg8		item.create	bn-1qty	{"description":"OBJECTIVE\nRe-run the SG2 benchmark; confirm wasted-turn metrics dropped to T2.7's\npre-registered targets; iterate T4.2 until met.\n\nACCEPTANCE CRITERIA\n- Targets met with benchmark evidence, or an explicit, justified\n  renegotiation of the target recorded.\n\nDEPENDS ON: T4.2.\n","kind":"task","labels":["v1-0","ergonomics"],"parent":"bn-2j45","size":"m","title":"T4.3 Re-benchmark; iterate to pre-registered targets"}	blake3:FnMqZ0VaBOIjcHayYLBDurbkk8COelCxY1VWWw5ev08
1778965660545868	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEysw8		item.create	bn-l6o7	{"description":"OBJECTIVE\nTurn the goal bn-142y hard gates into an explicit yes/no checklist with an\nowner per gate: Oracle A+B clean at the T1.9 soak target; regression seed\ncorpus (T1.8) catching; SG2 eval run under frozen pre-registration; layout\ndecision (T3.5) resolved; SG4 (T4.3) targets met.\n\nACCEPTANCE CRITERIA\n- Every gate is a binary check with an owner and a linked bone.\n\nDEPENDS ON: (informational links to T1.9, T2.8, T3.5, T4.3).\nCONTEXT POINTERS: goal bn-142y \"Hard gates\" section.\n","kind":"task","labels":["v1-0","release"],"parent":"bn-3ctu","size":"s","title":"T5.1 v1.0 acceptance-criteria doc (checkable gates)"}	blake3:Qw4uobEcWVuJauXCIxUck4Gg2OsopZPPRlSAGenOS-w
1778965660809297	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEytA8		item.create	bn-2uws	{"description":"OBJECTIVE\nWrite the public safety artifact: the two invariants, the soak volume, and\nthe bn-cm63 SELF-FOUND-BUG scar story (a harness that drew its own tool's\nblood is the credible claim; a clean author sweep is not). Publish the\nreproducible harness + the public seed range.\n\nACCEPTANCE CRITERIA\n- Writeup + harness + seeds are externally reproducible by a third party\n  from the published material.\n\nDEPENDS ON: T1.9.\nCONTEXT POINTERS: bn-cm63 (the scar) ; T1.9 soak results.\n","kind":"task","labels":["v1-0","release"],"parent":"bn-3ctu","size":"m","title":"T5.2 Safety-evidence publication (lead with the scar)"}	blake3:wa-Ie7U7Ap2Tnyjlw3OVsgLp4-btHv3D6sqYM9REITo
