1779737088914583	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy3BA		item.comment	bn-u9iy	{"body":"T2.8 ready (commit 9b8c9d3 in ws/bn-u9iy). FrictionList schema v1 + reducer + Markdown renderer in crates/maw-bench-metrics/src/friction_list.rs; sg2-friction-list bin; just sg2-friction-list-pilot wired. notes/sg2-friction-list.md scaffold (TEMPLATE-banner stamped) + notes/sg2-friction-list-handoff.md (top-K + validation-loop contract for SG4/T4.1). 66+2 tests pass; no_composite invariant lifted + asserted. Pilot top-3: ws_merge_structured_conflict, ws_sync_stale_workspace, epoch_sync_required (synthetic — real numbers land post-campaign). SG2 (bn-2jwi) ready to auto-close on merge — this was the last open child."}	blake3:IG6zgd1ml97TIIzf_3vje4jVkGByH9upc9xqafklL_U
1779737494449214	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyAQ		item.create	bn-yyx	{"description":"OBJECTIVE\nReduce the agent-turn-cost of `ws_merge_structured_conflict` — the\nhighest-ranked cluster in SG2's friction list — via the\nmerge-engine-resilience fix class.\n\nCLUSTER\n`ws_merge_structured_conflict` (per `MawVerbAttribution`,\n`crates/maw-bench-metrics/src/attribution.rs`). Fires when\n`maw ws merge ... --check` (or implicit merge) reports a structured\nconflict and the agent then issues a recovery op of the same class\non the same target — a wasted turn attributable to the merge surface.\n\nCURRENT MEASURED COST (pilot, synthetic)\nrank=1, total_cost_turns=9, runs=3. Source:\n`notes/sg2-friction-list.md` (T2.8) pilot ranking table. Real-run\nnumbers replace these once T2's real-LLM campaign produces\nfriction-bearing transcripts; the rank may shift but the cluster's\nhistory places it as a structural top-2 candidate.\n\nCANDIDATE MITIGATION CLASSES (from bn-2j45 review-pass-1)\n(1) structured-conflict workspace UX — first-class conflict-object\n    affordances (mirrors jj's first-class conflicts) so the agent\n    does not re-issue the same merge after a recoverable conflict;\n(4) append-only event log — `conflict_detected` /\n    `integration_started` / `integration_completed` events give the\n    agent oracle-quality \"what just happened\" without re-running;\n(8) mergeback queue — `maw integrate --queue/--next/--abort/--resume`\n    with provenance so a conflicted merge does not poison subsequent\n    attempts.\n\nTARGET METRIC DELTA\nReduce the attributed `ws_merge_structured_conflict`\n`total_cost_turns` by ≥ 50% at the next SG4 re-benchmark\n(T4.3 / bn-1qty), measured against the FrictionList JSON produced\nby `just sg2-friction-list <artifact-dir>`.\n\nEVIDENCE\n- `notes/sg2-friction-list.md` (T2.8 scaffold).\n- `notes/sg2-friction-list-handoff.md` (consumer contract;\n  cost-reduction stop condition: top-3 aggregate -50%).\n- `notes/sg4-fix-backlog.md` (this triage's audit-trail row).\n\nDEPENDENTS\nWire as `blocks` for T4.2 / bn-350o (rollup) — that task cannot\ndeclare \"harden complete\" until this fix ships.\n","kind":"task","labels":["ergonomics","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-2j45","size":"l","title":"Reduce ws_merge_structured_conflict cluster cost via merge-engine-resilience"}	blake3:tsP1Xkm_5p7I9G0TQKaca_HuxTWwQAU-qWmNm5_9b8g
1779737501432257	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyAg		item.create	bn-221b	{"description":"OBJECTIVE\nReduce the agent-turn-cost of `ws_sync_stale_workspace` via the\nstale-state-self-healing fix class.\n\nCLUSTER\n`ws_sync_stale_workspace`. Fires when `maw ws sync` is needed\nbecause the workspace went stale (epoch advanced underneath it)\nand the agent retried a verb that previously failed with a stale\nsignal — i.e. the agent paid a turn to discover staleness instead\nof being told.\n\nCURRENT MEASURED COST (pilot, synthetic)\nrank=2, total_cost_turns=3, runs=2. Source:\n`notes/sg2-friction-list.md` (T2.8) pilot ranking table.\n\nCANDIDATE MITIGATION CLASSES (from bn-2j45 review-pass-1)\n(2) `maw status --json` answering \"where am I / what other ws /\n    what stale / what to integrate\" in one call;\n(7) safe-cleanup state vocabulary\n    (clean / dirty-uncommitted / committed-unintegrated /\n    integrated / abandoned-with-snapshot) so the stale state is a\n    named first-class state, not an implicit failure mode;\n(4) append-only event log — `workspace_created` and the epoch\n    advance events let the agent reason about stale-ness without\n    guessing.\n\nTARGET METRIC DELTA\nReduce the attributed `ws_sync_stale_workspace` `total_cost_turns`\nby ≥ 50% at the next SG4 re-benchmark (T4.3 / bn-1qty).\n\nEVIDENCE\n- `notes/sg2-friction-list.md` (T2.8 scaffold).\n- `notes/sg2-friction-list-handoff.md` (consumer contract).\n- `notes/sg4-fix-backlog.md` (this triage's audit-trail row).\n\nDEPENDENTS\nWire as `blocks` for T4.2 / bn-350o.\n","kind":"task","labels":["ergonomics","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-2j45","size":"m","title":"Reduce ws_sync_stale_workspace cluster cost via stale-state-self-healing"}	blake3:BoZNfwhof6xTZQtgXPNH66nEdZHzWMltgLtSvpVtB10
1779737501675076	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyAw		item.create	bn-1ieb	{"description":"OBJECTIVE\nReduce the agent-turn-cost of `epoch_sync_required` via the\nepoch-auto-advance fix class.\n\nCLUSTER\n`epoch_sync_required`. Fires when `maw epoch sync` was needed\n(workspace's epoch baseline drifted from the integration branch).\nAgents often miss this step — the cluster names that miss.\n\nCURRENT MEASURED COST (pilot, synthetic)\nrank=3, total_cost_turns=3, runs=2. Source:\n`notes/sg2-friction-list.md` (T2.8) pilot ranking table.\n\nCANDIDATE MITIGATION CLASSES (from bn-2j45 review-pass-1)\n- Auto-advance the epoch when the integration branch moves\n  forward without a competing local change (architectural — fewer\n  cases requiring the verb at all);\n(3) `maw doctor` / `maw repair` coverage expansion — detect\n    \"mismatched base ref\" / \"missing .maw state\" and repair\n    without requiring the agent to invoke `epoch sync` manually;\n(4) append-only event log — surface \"epoch advanced\" as an event\n    the next workspace operation reads, not a state the agent\n    must poll for.\n\nTARGET METRIC DELTA\nReduce the attributed `epoch_sync_required` `total_cost_turns` by\n≥ 50% at the next SG4 re-benchmark (T4.3 / bn-1qty).\n\nEVIDENCE\n- `notes/sg2-friction-list.md` (T2.8 scaffold).\n- `notes/sg2-friction-list-handoff.md` (consumer contract).\n- `notes/sg4-fix-backlog.md` (this triage's audit-trail row).\n\nDEPENDENTS\nWire as `blocks` for T4.2 / bn-350o.\n","kind":"task","labels":["ergonomics","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-2j45","size":"m","title":"Reduce epoch_sync_required cluster cost via epoch-auto-advance"}	blake3:prJ8k7hknZND_ecn1etBsPbjDyE4boH20vArG2O6UOk
1779737501917053	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyBA		item.create	bn-1t17	{"description":"OBJECTIVE\nReduce the agent-turn-cost of `vocabulary_scarcity` via the\nverb-discoverability fix class. **This cluster is always\nincluded in the SG4 fix backlog regardless of measured cost** —\nsee \"Inclusion rule\" below.\n\nCLUSTER\n`vocabulary_scarcity`. Fires when the agent issues a verb /\nflag combination that doesn't exist in the maw CLI — captures\nthe \"scarce maw vocabulary\" friction from the agent-fluency\nmitigation: the agent had to discover the correct surface by\ntrial and error.\n\nCURRENT MEASURED COST (pilot, synthetic)\nrank=4, total_cost_turns=3, runs=2. Source:\n`notes/sg2-friction-list.md` (T2.8) pilot ranking table.\n\nINCLUSION RULE (always include)\nPer `memory:maw-design-rationale-agent-fluency` and the\nT2.8-friction-list \"Agent-fluency principle measurement\"\nsection: maw's self-describing, copy-pasteable output is the\n*load-bearing mitigation* for the training-data-scarce verb\nproblem. Whether that bet holds in the field is the live\nopen question. So this cluster gets a backlog entry even at\ncost=0 — its absence at next-bench is the *positive*\nevidence we are looking for, not noise to omit.\n\nCANDIDATE MITIGATION CLASSES (from bn-2j45 review-pass-1)\n(5) `maw crib <agent>` CLI emitting per-agent protocol so the\n    agent can ask the tool what it can do, in machine-friendly\n    form;\n(9) first-class overkill-line CLI guidance (\"use plain\n    Claude/Codex worktrees for one-off independent tasks; use\n    maw when N agents, overlapping files, or integration-queue\n    risk exceeds X\") — reduces the volume of agents reaching\n    for nonexistent verbs by giving the correct mental model\n    up front;\n- Continue investing in self-describing output (the load-bearing\n  mitigation per the agent-fluency rationale): every error path\n  includes the exact correct command to fix it.\n\nTARGET METRIC DELTA\nReduce the attributed `vocabulary_scarcity` `total_cost_turns`\nby ≥ 50% at the next SG4 re-benchmark (T4.3 / bn-1qty); if\ncost is already 0 at the real-run baseline, the target is\n\"remains 0 across the next two benches\" (stability evidence\nfor the agent-fluency mitigation).\n\nEVIDENCE\n- `notes/sg2-friction-list.md` (T2.8 scaffold; agent-fluency\n  measurement section).\n- `memory:maw-design-rationale-agent-fluency` (open thread).\n- `notes/sg2-friction-list-handoff.md` (consumer contract).\n- `notes/sg4-fix-backlog.md` (this triage's audit-trail row).\n\nDEPENDENTS\nWire as `blocks` for T4.2 / bn-350o.\n","kind":"task","labels":["ergonomics","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-2j45","size":"m","title":"Reduce vocabulary_scarcity cluster cost via verb-discoverability"}	blake3:e22jCoExYjOKzxdCqHjPOeb0iTe1sdIW12ugYjfaau0
1779737502191930	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyBQ		item.create	bn-29fi	{"description":"OBJECTIVE\nReduce the agent-turn-cost of `ws_recover_invoked` via the\ndestroy-prevention fix class.\n\nCLUSTER\n`ws_recover_invoked`. By definition a wasted-recovery turn (the\nagent's earlier destroy or sync left something that needed\nrescuing). The Prime Invariant means the work is preserved, but\nthe turn spent invoking `maw ws recover` is wasted relative to\nforward progress.\n\nCURRENT MEASURED COST (pilot, synthetic)\nrank=5, total_cost_turns=2, runs=2. Source:\n`notes/sg2-friction-list.md` (T2.8) pilot ranking table.\n\nCANDIDATE MITIGATION CLASSES (from bn-2j45 review-pass-1)\n(3) `maw doctor` + `maw repair` coverage expansion — detect\n    \"deleted WT dir / stale git WT metadata / orphaned ws /\n    concurrent maw lock\" pre-destroy so recover is not needed;\n(7) safe-cleanup state vocabulary — agents that name\n    `abandoned-with-snapshot` distinctly from `dirty-uncommitted`\n    are less likely to destroy work they then have to recover;\n(8) mergeback queue with provenance + overlap tracking — fewer\n    cases where the agent destroys a workspace whose work was\n    still queued.\n\nTARGET METRIC DELTA\nReduce the attributed `ws_recover_invoked` `total_cost_turns`\nby ≥ 50% at the next SG4 re-benchmark (T4.3 / bn-1qty).\n\nEVIDENCE\n- `notes/sg2-friction-list.md` (T2.8 scaffold).\n- `notes/sg2-friction-list-handoff.md` (consumer contract).\n- `notes/sg4-fix-backlog.md` (this triage's audit-trail row).\n\nDEPENDENTS\nWire as `blocks` for T4.2 / bn-350o.\n","kind":"task","labels":["ergonomics","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-2j45","size":"m","title":"Reduce ws_recover_invoked cluster cost via destroy-prevention"}	blake3:xRMHXxyeouDHHHswgQxHpZ1XHNBkCd8Mqd3Yx54X_1o
1779737502430196	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyBg		item.create	bn-c6l3	{"description":"OBJECTIVE\nReduce the agent-turn-cost of `ws_destroy_refused` via the\ndestroy-guidance-output fix class.\n\nCLUSTER\n`ws_destroy_refused`. `maw ws destroy` refused because the\nworkspace had unmerged changes (Prime Invariant guard); the\nagent then either re-issued with `--force` or worked around.\nThe refusal burns a turn even though it is correct behavior.\n\nCURRENT MEASURED COST (pilot, synthetic)\nrank=6, total_cost_turns=1, runs=1. Source:\n`notes/sg2-friction-list.md` (T2.8) pilot ranking table.\n\nCANDIDATE MITIGATION CLASSES (from bn-2j45 review-pass-1)\n- Self-describing output: every refusal message includes the\n  EXACT next command — `maw ws merge <name> --into default\n  --destroy` OR `maw ws destroy <name> --force` with explicit\n  Prime-Invariant snapshot reassurance — so the agent does not\n  need a second turn to decide;\n(7) safe-cleanup state vocabulary — `committed-unintegrated`\n    is a distinct named state, not \"destroy refused\";\n(2) `maw status --json` \"what to integrate\" answer pre-empts the\n    destroy attempt entirely.\n\nTARGET METRIC DELTA\nReduce the attributed `ws_destroy_refused` `total_cost_turns`\nby ≥ 50% at the next SG4 re-benchmark (T4.3 / bn-1qty); given\nthe very low absolute baseline, the practical target is\n\"reaches 0\" across the next two benches.\n\nEVIDENCE\n- `notes/sg2-friction-list.md` (T2.8 scaffold).\n- `notes/sg2-friction-list-handoff.md` (consumer contract).\n- `notes/sg4-fix-backlog.md` (this triage's audit-trail row).\n\nDEPENDENTS\nWire as `blocks` for T4.2 / bn-350o.\n","kind":"task","labels":["ergonomics","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-2j45","size":"s","title":"Reduce ws_destroy_refused cluster cost via destroy-guidance-output"}	blake3:I_xlLDSpwgGdHXxEJogkPQAPN4g_iF1HFILo4mRYGVo
1779737502666427	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyBw		item.create	bn-242l	{"description":"OBJECTIVE\nReduce the agent-turn-cost of `read_from_stale_workspace` via\nthe status-output-discoverability fix class.\n\nCLUSTER\n`read_from_stale_workspace`. Two-call window: agent read\n`maw ws status` / `list` / `diff` output but its next op was\ninconsistent with a stale workspace (e.g. tried to commit on a\nstale base then merge). The state was in the output; the agent\nmisread it.\n\nCURRENT MEASURED COST (pilot, synthetic)\nrank=7, total_cost_turns=1, runs=1. Source:\n`notes/sg2-friction-list.md` (T2.8) pilot ranking table.\n\nCANDIDATE MITIGATION CLASSES (from bn-2j45 review-pass-1)\n(1) machine-readable workspace manifest — agents that consume\n    structured state misread less often than agents that parse\n    prose;\n(2) `maw status --json` answering \"where am I / what other ws /\n    what stale / what to integrate\" in ONE call — the misread is\n    partly a \"scattered across N calls\" failure;\n(7) safe-cleanup state vocabulary — `committed-unintegrated`\n    and `dirty-uncommitted` named distinctly so the prose output\n    is unambiguous when an agent reads it instead of the JSON.\n\nTARGET METRIC DELTA\nReduce the attributed `read_from_stale_workspace`\n`total_cost_turns` by ≥ 50% at the next SG4 re-benchmark\n(T4.3 / bn-1qty); practical target \"reaches 0\" given the low\nbaseline.\n\nEVIDENCE\n- `notes/sg2-friction-list.md` (T2.8 scaffold).\n- `notes/sg2-friction-list-handoff.md` (consumer contract).\n- `notes/sg4-fix-backlog.md` (this triage's audit-trail row).\n\nDEPENDENTS\nWire as `blocks` for T4.2 / bn-350o.\n","kind":"task","labels":["ergonomics","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-2j45","size":"s","title":"Reduce read_from_stale_workspace cluster cost via status-output-discoverability"}	blake3:YlbcYItooDY0EdG5hOtwlFjkFH60fD9Rri5n_07KMck
1779737518827128	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyCA		item.link	bn-350o	{"link_type":"blocks","target":"bn-yyx"}	blake3:Mmmqw0d8IU3Z76phG1wL3Gs0JPdHeB5CkPY5X0NBBMw
