1779745611796287	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEygRE		item.comment	bn-242l	{"body":"Implemented status-output-discoverability fix: extended bn-221b's named\nLifecycleState + fix_command vocabulary into the three discovery\nsurfaces named by the cluster detector (`maw ws status --format json`,\n`maw ws list --format json`, `maw ws diff --json`), and added a\n`[lifecycle:<slug>]` token + paste-able Fix: line to the prose output\nof `ws status` / `ws list`. 12 new integration tests; full workspace\nsuite green (3188 passed, 0 failed); clippy clean. Target: ≥50%\nreduction at next-bench (T4.3 / bn-1qty); practical \"reaches 0\"."}	blake3:m_wrYrn8eAndBYOS-0u_9CykKGEIYirgYtQnBuVybcQ
1779745626180601	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyghE		item.comment	bn-29fi	{"body":"Implemented destroy-prevention surfaces (commit 86934f9 in ws/bn-29fi): (1) `maw ws destroy --dry-run [--format json]` returns a structured DestroyPreview (lifecycle_state, action, would_proceed, would_capture_snapshot, would_need_recovery, recommended_command, has_prior_snapshot) so agents probe before destroying — eliminates destroy→recover round-trip; (2) `LifecycleState::AbandonedWithSnapshot` (the missing safe-cleanup vocab variant from bn-2j45 review-pass-1) classifies destroyed-with-snapshot workspaces distinctly, with recover→merge as its fix_command; (3) `maw doctor` adds an `abandoned-with-snapshot` check naming the mergeback queue so it gets drained before more destroys; (4) destroy-refusal + force-destroy outputs name the merge-with-destroy alternative + the recover→merge two-step sequence. 3189 tests pass (clippy clean). 5 unit + 8 integration tests added. Cross-cluster trade: NONE (additive). Layout-agnostic (uses workspace_path/destroy_record helpers, no raw \"ws/\" strings) so coordination with T3.2 bn-2sw3 is clean. Lead: ready for merge review."}	blake3:wcRIgoQtGbOgfxGfd32uzl-l_pPQ0uWddLHmRu4KfXU
