1779745819018957	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyhRE		item.comment	bn-1t17	{"body":"Implemented verb-discoverability mitigation in ws/bn-1t17 (commit 0b640af). Two surfaces: (1) `maw crib <agent>` — new top-level subcommand emitting per-agent protocol (Markdown default; `--format json` for machine consumption; `--overkill-line` for the one-line 'when NOT to use maw' guidance). (2) Vocab-scarcity recovery hints — parse-failure path in main.rs now appends a `did you mean: <correct>  (<why>)` line plus universal-discovery tail (`maw --help` + `maw crib <agent>`) for 13 common training-data verbs (`ws new`, `checkout`, `stash`, `commit`, `rebase`, `merge <ws>`, top-level `bn`, etc.). Quarantine subverbs (`merge list|promote|abandon`) explicitly NOT hijacked. 32 unit tests + 5 integration tests added; cargo test --workspace = 3186 passed / 0 failed; clippy clean. Files: crates/maw-cli/src/{crib.rs, vocab_hints.rs} (new); main.rs + lib.rs (wiring). No raw `ws/` strings in runtime output (layout-agnostic; T3.2 / bn-2sw3 safe). Awaiting lead merge."}	blake3:Nr_GhJoavgedpxvhX9kG8xPULRHjoZiNakgEkQvB274
