1779748043800978	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyjRE		item.comment	bn-c6l3	{"body":"Implemented destroy-guidance-output: new DestroyRefusal payload in workspace/destroy_guidance.rs leads with the safe path (merge --destroy for committed-unintegrated, commit-then-merge for dirty-uncommitted), names the safe-cleanup vocab slug (bn-221b), inlines the Prime-Invariant reassurance for --force, and emits --format json. Refusal still refuses (Prime Invariant intact). 11 unit tests + 3 integration tests added; full workspace suite (3,166 tests) + clippy clean. Target delta: reaches 0 for ws_destroy_refused at next bench."}	blake3:SUCcYqn2qrHGiHaEFtYthNaXSTX10JWO7jhPICmFGvM
1779748290873133	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyjhE		item.comment	bn-1jqo	{"body":"T3.4 ready for lead review.\nAliases: collapsed Workspace+Ws into one variant with visible_aliases=[ws,worktree,wt]; all 4 entry forms route to same Commands::Workspace arm. `maw --help` shows `workspace    Manage agent workspaces [aliases: ws, worktree, wt]`.\nTests: 4 new (route-create, route-list, help-advertised, visible-aliases-pinned) + existing ws_merge_help test updated to canonical path. 3275/3275 pass, clippy clean.\nGuardrail: notes/t34-guardrail-patch.md documents 3 mechanisms (path-via-maw-exec, AGENTS.md, optional opt-in hook with MAW_AGENT_WORKSPACE interface). Lead applies patch to ws/default/AGENTS.md.\nT3.5 input: directional eval can use the patched AGENTS.md as treatment; SP5 bn-2kgu prototype's aliases now match real binary."}	blake3:AvCKROkpG--4XBXE0SRBBDcC41nz5hVOk2SQm-1csRw
