1779749109412104	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEykBE		item.create	bn-voy5	{"description":"Follow-up to bn-c6l3 (SG4 destroy-guidance-output). The destroy_guidance.rs\nmodule landed on main as a self-describing DestroyRefusal type with text +\nJSON renderers + 11 passing unit tests, but it is NOT wired into the actual\ndestroy() function — `--keep epoch` preserved bn-29fi's destroy-prevention\ncue text rather than swapping in bn-c6l3's structured refusal. The 3\nintegration tests asserting end-to-end refusal shape are #[ignore]d pending\nthis wire-up.\n\nAcceptance:\n1. `create.rs::destroy()` builds a `DestroyRefusal` and renders it\n   (text by default, JSON via new --format flag) — preserving bn-29fi's\n   existing cue lines (--dry-run pointer + merge --destroy alternative)\n   inside the new structured shape.\n2. `Destroy` subcommand in workspace/mod.rs gains `--format json|text|pretty`.\n3. destroy() signature: add `format: Option<OutputFormat>` parameter; update\n   2 callers in recover.rs + changes/mod.rs to pass None.\n4. Un-ignore the 3 integration tests in tests/destroy_gate.rs:\n   - bn_c6l3_refusal_for_dirty_workspace_leads_with_commit_then_merge\n   - bn_c6l3_refusal_for_committed_work_recommends_merge_and_destroy\n   - bn_c6l3_refusal_emits_machine_readable_json_under_format_flag\n5. Remove the TODO + `#![allow(dead_code)]` from destroy_guidance.rs.\n6. `cargo test --workspace` green; `cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings` clean.\n\nNon-goals:\n- No changes to the refusal SEMANTICS (still refuses; Prime Invariant intact).\n- No changes to bn-29fi's --dry-run flag or the AbandonedWithSnapshot vocab.\n\nPredecessors: bn-c6l3 (DestroyRefusal scaffold), bn-29fi (cue text + --dry-run).\n","kind":"task","labels":["ergonomics","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-2j45","size":"s","title":"Wire up destroy_guidance (bn-c6l3 follow-up): integrate DestroyRefusal payload with bn-29fi destroy-prevention cues"}	blake3:9rLkjXpCRdgzQ5MPRSgncA0wszad-2dJtJ5csKnR804
1779749319197114	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEykRE		item.comment	bn-3kkl	{"body":"Implemented `maw migrate` per §7 14-step algorithm (Phases A→E). New: crates/maw-cli/src/migrate.rs + migrate/journal.rs (crash-safe via .manifold/migration/journal.json → .maw/manifold/migration/journal.json post-flip); CLI subcommand `maw migrate [--resume] [--dry-run]`. Made oracle_b layout-aware (ws_dir_exists/manifold_dir_path) so DST oracles pass post-migration. Tests: tests/migrate.rs covers greenfield, populated (clean+dirty+committed-ahead), in-flight-merge-refusal, doctor-clean, no-op-on-consolidated, journal-resume, dry-run-noop. Verified: `cargo test --workspace` = 3270 pass / 0 fail; clippy --workspace --all-targets -D warnings clean; manual smoke (brownfield init --legacy-ws + workspace + dirty edit → migrate → doctor green; recovery ref pinned). Replaces jj-era upgrade.rs (kept for v1→v2, marked DEPRECATED). Decision: dirty ws/default's delta is pinned as recovery ref but NOT auto-replayed at root (avoids overlap conflicts mid-migration; user runs maw ws recover default --to default-prev to restore). Lead reviews/merges."}	blake3:OlzU00-zC-UL_3HNkcmQrQaaOGNdN5k7bfULfZ0CobA
