1779752682557975	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyoRE		item.create	bn-3uj4	{"description":"Per 2026-05-25 lead decision: NOT auto-cutting v1.0 final. v1.0-pre.1\nis a pre-release tag that bundles everything currently on main\n(SG1+SG2+SG3 complete, SG4 with the bn-voy5 wire-up follow-up\npending), gets installed locally for cross-project dogfooding, and\nis iterated on for a few weeks before v1.0 final.\n\nAcceptance:\n1. Workspace `Cargo.toml` version bumped to `1.0.0-pre.1` (workspace.version field).\n2. Internal path-dep `version =` requirements (ws/default/Cargo.toml + maw-cli/maw-core/maw-git/maw-scenario/maw-bench/maw-bench-adapters/maw-bench-metrics/maw-bench-sweep Cargo.toml) bumped in lockstep — `cargo build` breaks otherwise (per memory).\n3. CHANGELOG entry for v1.0-pre.1 listing the major milestones since v0.61.0:\n   - SG1 complete (Prime-Invariant DST instrument; bn-2yzz cron 1e8 accrual tracking)\n   - SG2 complete (agent-ergonomics benchmark instrument; pre-reg + 3 substrate adapters + metrics + sweep harness + friction list)\n   - SG3 complete (consolidated .maw/ layout default + maw migrate v2→consolidated + worktree/wt aliases + layout-eval go/no-go gate)\n   - SG4 mostly complete (7 fix-tasks shipped; bn-voy5 wire-up follow-up tracked)\n   - bn-cm63 scar story still leads the safety claim (publication forthcoming)\n4. Local install: `just install` (or `cargo install --path crates/maw-cli --force`) produces a `1.0.0-pre.1` binary.\n5. `maw release v1.0.0-pre.1` (per memory: the release command advances+pushes the branch and pushes the tag; assumes the bump is already committed). Tag pushed to origin.\n6. GitHub release published (pre-release flag ON) at the tag.\n\nHard rules:\n- Lead handles `maw release` and `gh release create --prerelease` manually.\n- Pre-release semver: `1.0.0-pre.1` (not `1.0-pre-1`; semver-conformant).\n- After cut: `maw epoch sync` (release is a direct-commit-to-default flow → epoch goes stale).\n\nNon-goals:\n- NOT v1.0 final.\n- NOT the publication artifact (SG5 owns that for v1.0 final).\n- NOT the real-LLM SG3/SG4 campaigns (those can run during dogfood window in parallel).\n\nPredecessors: bn-voy5 should merge first (bundles the c6l3 wire-up). If\nbn-voy5 slips, pre-1 can still cut without it (the destroy_guidance\nscaffold is already on main with #[allow(dead_code)]).\n","kind":"task","labels":["release","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"s","title":"Cut v1.0-pre.1 release tag — bundle everything done, install locally, start dogfood window"}	blake3:p2SHKTJWgsx_JEBdsH_uPqdaQDTsebMdfZKUzYhpOCY
1779752700384014	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyohE		item.create	bn-25db	{"description":"Per 2026-05-25 lead decision: between v1.0-pre.1 and v1.0 final, lead\ninstalls the pre-release across all their projects and dogfoods for a\nfew weeks. Each new friction class found becomes a bone under SG4\n(ergonomics) or SG3 (layout) per where it belongs; the fix lands; a\nnew v1.0-pre.X is cut; cycle repeats.\n\nAcceptance:\n1. v1.0-pre.1 installed locally per bn-3uj4.\n2. Lead uses it across personal projects (no specific count — judgment call).\n3. Each new friction class opens a small bone with reproducer + measured\n   impact (e.g. extra turns it cost, doctor warning it surfaced, etc.).\n4. Fixes land; pre-release version bumps (pre.2, pre.3, ...) cut along the way.\n5. When friction rate plateaus AND no v1.0-blocking finding open: lead\n   signals dogfood window closed; v1.0 final cut (SG5 / bn-3ctu) opens.\n6. Real-LLM SG3 go/no-go campaign (T3.5 bn-1uzn deliverable, ~$5–8 / 60 runs)\n   and SG4 re-bench (T4.3 bn-1qty deliverable, ~SG2-budget) can run during\n   this window without gating it. Their results land in the publication\n   artifact at v1.0 final.\n\nCalendar estimate: open-ended; lead signals close.\n\nHard rules:\n- Dogfood window is opt-in; lead controls cadence.\n- NO new v1.0 sub-goals get opened during this window (the SG1–SG5 surface\n  is frozen). New friction = small bone under SG3/SG4; not new sub-goal.\n\nPredecessors: bn-3uj4 (cut v1.0-pre.1).\nDependents: bn-3ctu (v1.0 final).\n","kind":"task","labels":["release","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"m","title":"v1.0 dogfood window — lead uses v1.0-pre.X across projects, captures friction, iterates"}	blake3:aWw-BppFSBm5wSf6n6knVTrVWgvupYpliBhoMNw_kco
1779752710647701	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyoxE		item.comment	bn-3ctu	{"body":"**2026-05-25 lead decision: SG5 is the v1.0 FINAL cut, NOT the pre-release.** The pre-release path is now: (1) bn-3uj4 cuts v1.0-pre.1 with everything currently on main; (2) bn-25db is the dogfood window — lead uses pre.X across projects, iterates, opens small bones under SG3/SG4 for friction found, cuts further pre.N as needed; (3) bn-3ctu (THIS bone, SG5) cuts v1.0 final after dogfood signals plateau + publication artifact drafted. SG5's deliverables (safety-evidence writeup with bn-cm63 scar lead, crossover-curve writeup, docs/README/AGENTS.md final pass, version bump 1.0.0 + CHANGELOG, release cut) all happen at the FINAL cut, not pre-release."}	blake3:0RToSJaQjsxUa3nso7b3pjk_HFrGkWy-34kWE3wQAUo
