1779820879945447	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEytRE		item.create	bn-3kxq	{"description":"Per 2026-05-26 lead decision: replace the ClaudeBackend stub in\ncrates/maw-bench/src/claude.rs with a working `claude -p\n--output-format json` subprocess wire BEFORE v1.0-pre.1 cuts, so the\nSG3 layout go/no-go + SG4 re-bench campaigns can run during the\ndogfood window.\n\nCurrent state (verified 2026-05-26):\n- ClaudeBackend.run is a stub that errors unless MAW_BENCH_ALLOW_REAL_LLM=1\n- Even with that env, the call body is a TODO (\"T2.6 replaces this\")\n- All in-repo tests run via MockAgent (deterministic, no LLM cost)\n\nArchitecture (frozen via SP3 / bn-2ixm):\n- subprocess pattern: `claude -p --output-format json` (NOT direct\n  Anthropic API — we want Claude Code's actual tool surface driving\n  git/maw/jj, not a reimplemented tool loop)\n- per AgentBackend.run: one invocation per scenario run, not per\n  PlannedStep; the agent's task prompt is the rendered scenario; the\n  agent's tool calls (Bash, Read, Edit, Write, Glob, Grep) drive the\n  substrate\n- cwd is the SubstrateHandle.workspace_root\n- SP3 documented \"--bare breaks OAuth\" — verify against your local CC\n  install before declaring done\n\nAcceptance:\n1. ClaudeBackend.run spawns `claude -p --cwd <ws> --output-format json\n   --allowed-tools \"Bash,Read,Edit,Write,Glob,Grep\" <prompt>` (exact\n   flag spelling per current CC; verify with `claude -p --help`).\n2. Streams the JSON envelope; parses message_start / content_block /\n   message_stop into the AgentTurn{reply_text, tool_calls[]} shape.\n3. Captures usage from the final envelope → AgentReply.cost_usd.\n4. Honors AgentConfig: model (--model), max_turns (post-stream check\n   or upstream flag if CC supports), max_budget_usd (post-stream\n   check), temperature (--temperature if exposed; document if not),\n   permission_mode (--permission-mode or equivalent).\n5. Defence-in-depth guard preserved: real LLM dispatch still requires\n   MAW_BENCH_ALLOW_REAL_LLM=1 env in ADDITION to the claude-backend\n   feature.\n6. New #[ignore]-gated integration test\n   `tests/claude_backend_smoke.rs` that runs a single trivial\n   scenario against the real `claude` binary if present + env set.\n   Test budget: <$0.10. Documents the cost in the test source.\n7. Run the smoke test ONCE manually (lead-authorized; not in CI)\n   against your local CC install to verify end-to-end; paste the\n   stdout in the bone comment as evidence.\n8. cargo check (no features) + cargo check -p maw-bench --features\n   bench,claude-backend + cargo test -p maw-bench --features bench\n   (still MockAgent-only) — all green.\n9. cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings clean.\n\nNon-goals (deferred):\n- Multi-turn budget enforcement beyond AgentConfig.max_turns/max_budget_usd\n- Streaming back-pressure / cancellation mid-turn\n- Anthropic-API direct path (subprocess pattern is chosen for v1.0)\n- Actually RUNNING the 60-run SG3 campaign or the SG4 re-bench — those\n  are dogfood-window calendar artifacts\n\nPredecessors: bn-1sqo (T2.2 harness + stub), bn-2ixm (SP3 invocation pattern), bn-3l1f (T2.6 sweep needs this)\nDependents: bn-3uj4 (v1.0-pre.1 cut blocks on this)\n","kind":"task","labels":["benchmark","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"m","title":"Wire ClaudeBackend to claude -p subprocess — replace T2.2/T2.6 stub before v1.0-pre.1"}	blake3:FwGZ3uYelnhp62IRDgdqGMuB6XvNblTZ-GUybsnwAts
