1779826918088593	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyuxE		item.create	bn-3w0c	{"description":"Per 2026-05-26 lead decision: enable cross-model comparison\n(haiku/sonnet/opus) without per-campaign re-pin. Backend already\naccepts any CC-supported model string (bn-3kxq wired `--model\n<AgentConfig.model>`); only the sweep + recipes are hardcoded to\nAgentConfig::default() (sonnet).\n\nCurrent state (verified 2026-05-26):\n- crates/maw-bench-sweep/src/driver.rs:172 — `let agent_config =\n  maw_bench::agent::AgentConfig::default();` (no override path)\n- just sg3-layout-eval / sg4-rebench / sg2-sweep recipes don't expose\n  model selection\n\nAcceptance:\n1. SweepDriver constructor / run-config accepts an\n   `Option<AgentConfig>` override (defaults to AgentConfig::default()\n   when None, preserving SP3 pin).\n2. Just recipes accept `MODEL` env var (or `--model` if cleaner) →\n   plumbs into the override. Default behavior unchanged (sonnet).\n3. `sg3_layout_eval`, `sg4_rebench`, `sg2_sweep` binaries (whichever\n   exist) accept the override flag/env and pass it through.\n4. The §6.4 manifest in each BenchRun JSON already records `model` —\n   verify the override flows through (no code change should be\n   needed; this is an audit AC).\n5. Cross-model comparison guidance in `notes/sg2-benchmark-preregistration.md`\n   (or a new short doc): \"per-campaign pinning is the dominance contract;\n   cross-model curves are published as separate campaigns, NOT folded\n   into the same sweep\". The model-axis flag is a one-shot spot-check\n   tool, NOT a substitute for separate per-model campaigns.\n6. Test: small unit/integration test that drives the SweepDriver with\n   a non-default model override + asserts the BenchRun manifest\n   records it. (MockAgent only; no real-LLM cost.)\n7. cargo check (no features) + cargo test --workspace + cargo clippy\n   --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings — all green.\n\nUse cases this unblocks:\n- Spot-check the SG3 subset against haiku before committing sonnet\n  quota for the full 60-run campaign.\n- Spot-check the SG4 re-bench against opus for the highest-cost\n  cluster only, to see if fix efficacy holds at the largest model.\n- Compare across models as a v1.x follow-on without re-plumbing.\n\nNon-goals:\n- Re-pinning the SP3-anchored default (still sonnet).\n- Auto-comparing curves across models (separate-campaign discipline preserved).\n- Adding model as a real condition-spectrum axis in the sweep grid\n  (that conflates substrate-effect with model-effect — explicitly out).\n\nPredecessors: bn-3kxq (ClaudeBackend wire — done).\nDoes NOT block: bn-3uj4 (v1.0-pre.1 cut) — pre.1 can ship with this\nopen; lead can dispatch before or during dogfood window.\n","kind":"task","labels":["benchmark","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"xs","title":"Model-as-an-axis: plumb --model override through sweep driver + just recipes"}	blake3:UCt1kw0rb1yY5FWdhbtJNzBSyUEP1ORjdrJUIIetO3U
1779840917472337	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyvBE		item.create	bn-1h4b	{"description":"Per 2026-05-26 lead discovery: bn-3kxq wired ClaudeBackend (real-LLM\nsubprocess driver) and bn-1uzn/bn-3l1f wired the eval-driving bins,\nbut the two layers were never connected. Both bins hardcode\n`MockAgent + NoopSubstrate`; the `--pilot` flag only toggles N, not\nbackend or substrate. Real-LLM eval is currently impossible without\nre-plumbing.\n\nCurrent state (verified 2026-05-26):\n- crates/maw-bench-sweep/src/bin/sg3_layout_eval.rs:67 — only\n  imports MockAgent, MockScript, NoopSubstrate\n- crates/maw-bench-sweep/src/bin/sg2_sweep_pilot.rs:33 — same\n- ClaudeBackend lives in maw_bench::claude::ClaudeBackend (bn-3kxq);\n  gated behind claude-backend feature + MAW_BENCH_ALLOW_REAL_LLM=1\n- Real adapters exist in maw-bench-adapters: MawAdapter (consolidated\n  + legacy), WorktreesConventionAdapter, JjAdapter\n\nAcceptance:\n1. Introduce a `BackendChoice` enum (or similar) in maw-bench-sweep\n   (or the bin module) — variants Mock, Claude. Default = Mock for\n   backward compatibility (existing `just sg3-layout-eval-pilot` /\n   `sg2-sweep-pilot` behavior unchanged).\n2. New `--real-llm` flag on both bins. Selects Claude backend; requires\n   `claude-backend` feature compiled in + MAW_BENCH_ALLOW_REAL_LLM=1\n   env (defence-in-depth from bn-3kxq preserved). Without `--real-llm`,\n   bins behave exactly as today.\n3. New `--substrate=maw|worktrees|jj|noop` flag (or aliases).\n   `--real-llm` defaults to `--substrate=maw` if not specified (we\n   need a real substrate to exercise real verbs). `--pilot` defaults\n   to noop (MockAgent has nothing to drive on a real substrate).\n4. Layout selection in sg3-layout-eval (--layout=old|new|both)\n   translates to MawAdapter with consolidated vs legacy flavor —\n   when --real-llm is set. Use MawAdapter's existing flavor\n   parameter, not a separate adapter variant.\n5. New just recipes (additive — don't break existing pilots):\n   - `sg3-layout-eval-real n_a='3' n_b='3'`: real-LLM variant, defaults\n     to --n-a=3 --n-b=3 for cheapest first run (overridable).\n   - `sg2-sweep-real n='3'`: real-LLM variant of sweep pilot.\n   Both require MAW_BENCH_ALLOW_REAL_LLM=1 in env (else the bn-3kxq\n   guard errors out — that's the contract).\n6. Per-run cost capture: each BenchRun JSON already records cost_usd\n   (bn-3kxq wired this from CC's final envelope). Verify the sweep\n   summary aggregates it into total_cost_usd at the report level.\n7. Single smoke run of `sg3-layout-eval-real` with n_a=1 n_b=1 (2\n   real-LLM runs total, ~5 min, ~$0.10-0.20 if billed) against\n   lead's CC subscription. Paste stdout in bone comment as evidence.\n8. cargo check (no features) + cargo check -p maw-bench-sweep\n   --features bench,claude-backend + cargo test --workspace + cargo\n   clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings — all green.\n\nNon-goals:\n- Full SG3 60-run campaign (calendar work, separate dispatch).\n- SG4 re-bench plumbing (T4.3's sg4-rebench reads BenchRun dirs,\n  not the bins — separate wire-up if needed; likely just point it\n  at sg3-layout-eval-real outputs).\n- Cross-model parameter (bn-3w0c is the model-axis bone).\n\nPredecessors: bn-3kxq (ClaudeBackend), bn-1uzn (sg3 eval bin), bn-3l1f (sg2 sweep bin), bn-mit2 (adapters).\nBlocks: bn-3uj4 (v1.0-pre.1 cut) — lead wants real-LLM eval runnable before pre.1.\n","kind":"task","labels":["benchmark","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"m","title":"Wire ClaudeBackend + real substrate adapters into sg3-layout-eval + sg2-sweep-pilot bins"}	blake3:la44MOlN0EZTFVbnnGJF5BdNL2CpcLZp73TmxXorrTo
