1779889060166881	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEywhE		item.create	bn-2ert	{"description":"2026-05-26 SG3 frozen-N eval flagged NO-GO on R6 interventions:\n- C0 (benign): old=20 vs new=20 (equivalent)\n- C2 (moderate hostility): old=0 vs new=10/10 (smoking gun)\n\n10/10 means EVERY new-layout run at C2 triggered an intervention,\nwhile ZERO old-layout runs did. Not \"the layout is slightly slower\" —\nthis is a specific failure mode the new layout introduces under\nmoderate hostility that the old layout doesn't have.\n\nHypotheses (root-cause candidates per SP5 §6 risks):\nH1. Path-length doubling (SP5 risk #2): agents working at .maw/workspaces/<n>/...\n    may misread cwd vs at ws/<n>/. C2's overlapping-edit friction triggers\n    the misread under merge contention.\nH2. Hidden-dir invisibility (SP5 risk #1): agents don't see .maw/ in plain\n    ls output; can't find maw state path naturally.\nH3. AGENTS.md root-vs-stub (SP5 risk #3): consolidated layout missing or\n    different guidance vs v2-shipped stub; less-helpful default at C2.\nH4. NEW failure mode unrelated to SP5: T3.2 introduced something unpredicted.\n\nEvidence: notes/eval-real-2026-05-26/sg3/maw-{old,new}-layout/C2-T0/*.json\nEach BenchRun JSON carries the full agent transcript (per-turn reply text\n+ tool_calls + final verdict + oracle_b summary). Per-run inspection of\nwhich intervention fired and what the agent was doing reveals the mechanism.\n\nAcceptance:\n1. Read all 10 new-layout C2 + 10 old-layout C2 BenchRun JSONs.\n2. Identify what counted as an intervention — per T2.5 attribution, proxy\n   from work_redone_turns × n. Trace exact mechanism per run.\n3. Classify each new-layout intervention against H1-H4 (or open H5+).\n4. Write notes/sg3-no-go-rootcause.md documenting: mechanism, hypothesis\n   support, recommended fix class, in-scope-for-v1.0 or not.\n5. Update bn-3uj4 with layout-default recommendation based on root cause.\n\nNon-goals: implementing the fix (separate bone), re-running SG3 eval,\ntouching ws/default/ source.\n\nHard rules: forensic not exploratory; don't run new evals; propose layout\ndefault, don't decide unilaterally.\n\nPredecessors: 2026-05-26 SG3 eval data (committed)\nBlocks: bn-3uj4 (v1.0-pre.1 cut)\n","kind":"task","labels":["layout","benchmark","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"m","title":"Investigate SG3 NO-GO root cause: why does .maw/ layout trigger 10/10 interventions at C2?"}	blake3:2KhVG_dREQfGPAm8VUs3KZ0gp-S2EbKQNWjfPh6tIQw
1779889084990539	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEywxE		item.create	bn-1te0	{"description":"2026-05-26 SG2 cross-arm pilot at N=3 showed maw dominating efficiency\nat BOTH C0 (benign) AND C4 (hostile). The \"overkill regime\" the\npre-reg said we'd publish (cells where maw loses on efficiency) is\ninvisible at this N.\n\nTwo possibilities:\n(a) Overkill regime exists but N=3 is too small to surface it\n    (medians within range overlap; rate metrics with Wilson UB 0.561\n    are uninformative).\n(b) Overkill regime doesn't exist in the bn-iux4 / T2.7 frozen grid\n    — maw's per-verb cost is structurally lower than worktrees+convention\n    AND jj at every cell we measured.\n\nEither way: ship the right answer in the v1.0 publication. (b) is\na STRONGER claim than the pre-reg promised — publish it confidently\nif true; admit (a) if power-limited.\n\nAcceptance:\n1. Run sg2-sweep-real at N=10 across all 3 substrates (maw, worktrees,\n   jj) into a shared persistent artifact dir, mirroring 2026-05-26's\n   N=3 pattern but bigger.\n2. Expected wall: ~50-70 min; cost ~$8-15 token-equivalent.\n3. Aggregator output (sg2-friction-list or sg2-report) committed to\n   notes/eval-real-YYYY-MM-DD-sg2-n10/ alongside per-run BenchRun JSONs.\n4. Document the verdict in notes/sg2-overkill-finding.md:\n   - Either \"overkill regime visible at cells X — published per pre-reg §2\"\n   - OR \"overkill regime not visible at N=10 across frozen grid — published\n     as 'maw dominates broadly' with the N=10 caveat (per-cell Wilson UB\n     3.84e-2 on rate metrics, paired-bootstrap CI on medians)\"\n5. Updates notes/sg2-benchmark-preregistration.md §2 with the empirical\n   answer to the \"publish-the-loss-regime\" commitment.\n\nNon-goals:\n- Full SG2 publication-grade campaign (N=20+, all cells in the spectrum)\n  — that's a calendar follow-on after v1.0 final.\n- Cross-model sweep (bn-3w0c).\n- SG2 conditions beyond C0+C4 (T2.6 / bn-3l1f's frozen pilot grid is\n  what we measure against; the full spectrum is a SG5 deliverable).\n\nPredecessors: bn-1h4b (eval-bin wire), 2026-05-26 SG2 N=3 data.\nBlocks: bn-3uj4 (v1.0-pre.1 cut) — pre.1 ships with this evidence in hand.\n","kind":"task","labels":["benchmark","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"s","title":"SG2 cross-arm at N=10: surface (or rule out) the overkill regime properly"}	blake3:A_EDkoCcYIZHLgmimnGZjfCFkZLcwGic68YAw4l64Ww
