1779889746590530	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyyBE		item.comment	bn-2ert	{"body":"ROOT CAUSE: substrate/binary version-skew (NEW hypothesis H5; H1-H3 REFUTED). The SG3 eval ran against installed maw v0.61.0 which predates T3.2 (commit 42d7ca66) — v0.61.0's doctor flags simulated .maw/ as foreign and 'Run: maw init'; 9/10 new-layout runs followed that advice in turn 2, migrating the substrate to v2 ws/ before any task ran. The 10v0 R6 spread is median×n amplifying ONE extra heuristic fire (r007's --force destroy chain whose description text contained 'recovery'). Fix: install post-T3.2 main HEAD locally + rerun SG3; v1.0-pre.1 keeps .maw/ default (option c). Full writeup: notes/sg3-no-go-rootcause.md (in ws bn-2ert, not yet merged)."}	blake3:JhZEFRlV4k9Ymhf87ZPS2rSq7uTNRrkkH6NmnzdenD8
1779889755837788	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyyRE		item.comment	bn-3uj4	{"body":"LAYOUT-DEFAULT RECOMMENDATION (from bn-2ert root-cause): KEEP T3.2 .maw/ as the v1.0 default (do NOT revert). The 2026-05-26 SG3 NO-GO was a measurement artifact — eval ran with installed v0.61.0 binary that predates T3.2 (commits 42d7ca66, f6cf96c1, 241231e3 all post-v0.61.0); v0.61.0 maw doctor refused the .maw/ substrate and instructed 9/10 agents to 'maw init', collapsing the simulation to v2 in turn 2. ACTION ITEM for pre.1: after 'just install' (acceptance #4) and BEFORE 'maw release v1.0.0-pre.1' (acceptance #5), rerun 'just sg3-layout-eval' against the pre.1 binary and attach the rerun verdict to the GitHub release notes superseding the 2026-05-26 NO-GO. Expected outcome: GO. See notes/sg3-no-go-rootcause.md §6 (ws bn-2ert)."}	blake3:z30qZ8UefjmNviAizjLieJxJWc1q18PAsGe1jgOsHDs
