1779889867076227	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyyxE		item.create	bn-f5zu	{"description":"2026-05-27 SG3 NO-GO investigation (bn-2ert) found the root cause was\nbinary/substrate version skew — the eval ran against installed maw\nv0.61.0 while the SUBSTRATE was the post-T3.2 .maw/ layout. The\nBenchRun.manifest.maw_version field exists per §6.4 but is empty in\nevery published BenchRun. A populated field would have caught this\nconfound at-source rather than via 20-run forensic trace.\n\nAcceptance:\n1. ClaudeBackend (or wherever the manifest is built) captures\n   `maw --version`, `git --version`, `jj --version` once per run\n   and writes into BenchRun.manifest fields.\n2. New fields: maw_version (already exists per agent comments —\n   just populate it), git_version (already in manifest schema),\n   jj_version (already in manifest schema). All read once per\n   ClaudeBackend.run; if a binary is missing or errors, record\n   the literal error string (don't crash the run).\n3. Eval bins (sg3-layout-eval, sg2-sweep-pilot) get a soft preflight\n   warning if the installed `maw` version is older than the source\n   tree version — e.g. compare against env!(\"CARGO_PKG_VERSION\") or\n   the workspace.version. Warning, not error (users may intentionally\n   bench an older binary). Emits the version pair to stderr at\n   bin startup if drift detected.\n4. Test: synthetic BenchRun JSON with populated maw_version field\n   round-trips through the parser; field documented in the §6.4\n   manifest sample in notes/sg2-benchmark-preregistration.md or\n   similar.\n5. cargo check + cargo test --workspace + cargo clippy --workspace\n   --all-targets -- -D warnings — all green.\n\nNon-goals:\n- Force re-run of existing pre-fix BenchRuns (the 2026-05-26 data\n  is committed as historical evidence; new runs get the new\n  instrumentation).\n- Hard-error on version skew (warn only; users may intentionally\n  bench older).\n\nPredecessors: bn-2ert (root cause documented), bn-3kxq (ClaudeBackend).\nBlocks: bn-3uj4 (v1.0-pre.1 cut) — lead wants version-skew catchable\nat source before pre.1 ships.\n","kind":"task","labels":["benchmark","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"s","title":"Populate BenchRun.manifest.maw_version + worktrees_git_version + jj_version (catch version skew at source)"}	blake3:A33kJnq4LLQ4mnU17iXWgM5jrU4ThX3BdRZJIMD4NMU
