1779908511632838	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy1BE		item.create	bn-1pzb	{"description":"2026-05-27 SG3 re-run against post-T3.2 installed binary REPRODUCED\nthe R6 C2 interventions failure (old=0, new=10/10). bn-2ert's H5\n(version skew) was at most a partial cause — the layout itself,\nmeasured against the binary that understands it, still triggers\nexactly 1 work-redone turn per C2 new-layout run while old-layout\ntriggers 0. C0 cells equivalent; turns + tool_calls equivalent;\nonly R6 differs.\n\nThree live hypotheses (in order of cheapest-to-check):\n\nH6. ADAPTER-SUBSTRATE MISMATCH: ConsolidatedLayoutAdapter is a\n    SIMULATED .maw/ shape built with raw git worktree primitives\n    (per SP5/bn-2kgu) — NOT what `maw init --consolidated` creates.\n    The post-T3.2 binary expects a specific .maw/manifold/ schema\n    that the adapter's mock may not faithfully reproduce.\n    CHECK: read crates/maw-bench-adapters/src/consolidated_layout_adapter.rs\n    + compare to what `maw init --consolidated` writes in a tempdir.\n\nH7. REAL C2-INDUCED REGRESSION (per-cell mechanism): something\n    about C2's overlap-rate + the .maw/ layout shape makes the\n    agent specifically retry merges. CHECK: forensic read of the\n    10 C2 new-layout BenchRuns from the re-run\n    (notes/eval-real-2026-05-27/sg3-rerun/maw-new-layout/C2-T0/*.json)\n    vs the 10 old-layout BenchRuns at C2.\n\nH8. ATTRIBUTION HEURISTIC ARTIFACT: the work_redone_turns ×n proxy\n    that R6 reads is misclassifying something benign on new layout.\n    CHECK: re-run T2.5's attribute_tool_call on the same transcripts;\n    identify what the heuristic counted and whether the agent\n    actually re-did work or just looked like it.\n\nAcceptance:\n1. Read consolidated_layout_adapter.rs source; compare its setup\n   output to a tempdir-spawned `maw init --consolidated` run.\n   Document any divergence (file paths created, contents,\n   .gitignore, .manifold-vs-.maw symlinks, etc.). If divergent: H6\n   supported, fix the adapter; if equivalent: H6 refuted.\n2. Read all 10 C2 new-layout BenchRun JSONs from the rerun + the\n   corresponding old-layout runs. For each new-layout run, trace\n   exactly which turn/tool-call triggered the attribution\n   heuristic to classify as work_redone. Find the common pattern.\n3. Classify each fired attribution against H6/H7/H8 (or H9+ if\n   a new mechanism emerges).\n4. Write notes/sg3-no-go-rootcause-v2.md (sequel to bn-2ert's doc):\n   - §0 Summary: 1-sentence root cause + recommended fix + v1.0\n     layout-default recommendation (revised).\n   - §1 H6 adapter-substrate check (with diff if divergent).\n   - §2 H7 mechanism trace (per-run from transcripts).\n   - §3 H8 attribution heuristic check.\n   - §4 Verdict: which Hn(s) survive.\n   - §5 Fix recommendation: layout itself bug fix; OR adapter fix\n     and re-run; OR attribution-heuristic v2 update; OR layout\n     genuinely worse on this metric, ship ws/ for v1.0.\n   - §6 v1.0-pre.1 recommendation for bn-3uj4 (revised from bn-2ert's).\n5. Update bn-3uj4 with the v2 recommendation.\n\nNon-goals:\n- Running new evals from this bone (forensic only; user owns the\n  next-eval call).\n- Implementing any fix (separate bone after diagnosis).\n\nHard rules:\n- Forensic, not exploratory.\n- Don't decide v1.0 layout default unilaterally — propose, lead\n  decides.\n\nPredecessors: bn-2ert (first investigation), bn-1h4b (eval wire-up),\n2026-05-27 SG3 re-run data (committed at notes/eval-real-2026-05-27/sg3-rerun/).\nBlocks: bn-3uj4 (v1.0-pre.1 cut) — lead wants this resolved before pre.1\ndecision on layout default.\n","kind":"task","labels":["layout","benchmark","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"m","title":"Investigate SG3 NO-GO reproduction — same R6 C2 fail with post-T3.2 binary, H5 only partial"}	blake3:ILFlVaAVbntwUM1XpgVx7uDk5ve-mbUjqRzLQgSF8IU
