1779909323187557	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy2xE		item.create	bn-27ai	{"description":"2026-05-27 bn-1pzb investigation confirmed H8: the SG3 R6 NO-GO\nreported \"10 vs 0 interventions\" was a 3-layer metric-pipeline\ndefect, not a real layout regression. Raw per-replicate fire counts\nare 7 vs 6 — within R6's \"no net increase\" noise floor.\n\nThree fixes, all in the metric pipeline (no eval re-run needed):\n\nFix A.1 (~5 LOC): `is_maw_arm` recognises `maw@<flavor>` arms.\n  Location: `crates/maw-bench-metrics/src/extract.rs:116`\n  Current: `arm == \"maw\" || arm.starts_with(\"maw-\")`\n  Wanted:  add `|| arm.starts_with(\"maw@\")` (or whatever matches\n           the eval arm-name convention; check sg3_layout_eval.rs).\n  Effect: SG3's maw@old-layout and maw@new-layout arms now route\n          through T2.5 attribute_tool_call (the real attribution),\n          not the substring fallback.\n\nFix A.2 (~10 LOC): task-aware recover attribution.\n  Location: `crates/maw-bench-metrics/src/attribution.rs::attribute_tool_call`\n  Problem: WsRecoverInvoked cluster fires whenever the agent runs\n           `maw ws recover`, even if the scenario task ASKED them\n           to recover (correct execution → false-positive friction).\n  Approach (α — cheapest): when the prior step's intent was a\n           recover-task, suppress the WsRecoverInvoked classification.\n           Requires looking back one tool-call or accepting the\n           current heuristic and subtracting expected recover events\n           in the R6 aggregator.\n  Approach (β — cleaner, deferred): thread `task_intended` through\n           ToolCall.attributed_op so the attribution function has\n           intent context. Tracked separately if α is enough for R6.\n\nFix A.3 (~5 LOC): sum_proxy uses raw per-replicate sum, not median×n.\n  Location: `crates/maw-bench-sweep/src/sg3_decision.rs:721`\n  Current: `total = median * n` — integer-truncates 1-bit median\n           deltas into n-bit total deltas.\n  Wanted:  `total = sum(per_replicate_values)` — already promised\n           in the doc-comment (\"v2/v3 will split via real per-\n           replicate sum\"). Lift that to v1 now.\n  Effect: 5 RC-tasks fired vs 4 → real sum 5 vs 4 (or 7v6 raw,\n          depending on how the value gets there), not 10 vs 0.\n\nAcceptance:\n1. The 3 fixes land in one commit.\n2. Unit tests:\n   - is_maw_arm recognises maw@old-layout and maw@new-layout.\n   - attribute_tool_call (or aggregator) doesn't classify a\n     task-intended recover as WsRecoverInvoked friction (test with\n     a synthetic ToolCall that follows a recover-task).\n   - sum_proxy returns raw sum, not median×n; existing tests that\n     assert the median×n behavior get updated with rationale.\n3. Re-run the SG3 decision OFFLINE against the committed\n   2026-05-27 rerun data (notes/eval-real-2026-05-27/sg3-rerun/).\n   New decision.json should show R6 C2 PASS (raw 7 vs 6 within\n   \"no net increase\" or near-equivalent).\n4. Updated decision.json + delta doc committed under\n   notes/eval-real-2026-05-27/sg3-rerun-recomputed/.\n5. cargo check + cargo test --workspace + cargo clippy --workspace\n   --all-targets -- -D warnings — all green.\n\nNon-goals:\n- Fix B (pair seeds across arms) — deferred to v1.0-final or\n  separate bone (it's a cleaner methodological fix but won't\n  flip THIS specific verdict).\n- Fix C (real maw init --consolidated in ConsolidatedLayoutAdapter)\n  — deferred to v1.1; the simulated adapter has methodological\n  debt but doesn't cause R6.\n\nPredecessors: bn-1pzb (root-cause v2 investigation, just merged).\nBlocks: bn-3uj4 (v1.0-pre.1 cut) — lead wants corrected verdict\nbefore cutting pre.1 with .maw/ default.\n","kind":"task","labels":["benchmark","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"s","title":"Fix SG3 metric pipeline (H8): is_maw_arm + task-aware recover attribution + sum_proxy raw-sum"}	blake3:5mAumXXIB_rXVbMbivJUdXR17eMe-XZSIZ5zzVBoUro
