1779912830976003	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy4hE		item.create	bn-232g	{"description":"2026-05-27 lead correction: maw is not \"the right tool sometimes\" —\nit's the workspace tool that replaces git-worktrees+convention. The\nbn-1t17 crib (and the bn-2j45 review-pass-1 comment #9 it was built\nfrom) frames maw as overkill for one-off tasks; that's misaligned\nwith the actual product vision and the SG2 N=10 evidence\n(no overkill regime emerged at sonnet across the pre-registered\ncells; maw is efficiency-dominant at both C0 benign and C4 hostile).\n\nAcceptance:\n1. Rewrite the crib's `## When NOT to use maw` section.\n   - Either DROP it entirely OR replace with affirmative `## When\n     to use maw` framing: maw is the workspace tool; use it for\n     every task; multiple agents work in isolated workspaces;\n     merge back via the Prime Invariant.\n   - Concrete wording the lead can iterate; default to dropping\n     the section + adding a one-line intro affirming maw as the\n     default workflow.\n2. Drop the `--overkill-line` flag on `maw crib`. It currently\n   prints \"use plain Claude/Codex worktrees for one-off...\" which\n   is exactly the framing being retracted.\n3. Update the affected unit tests in crib.rs that asserted\n   overkill-line-prefix presence + the overkill-text content.\n   New tests assert the absence of the deprecated framing + the\n   presence of the new wording.\n4. Update markdown sample in tests/integration that exercises the\n   full output (if present).\n5. Bone-comment-update on bn-1t17 + bn-2j45 noting the realignment\n   (bn-2j45's review-pass-1 #9 is retracted; track here).\n\nNon-goals (deferred to separate bones if lead wants them):\n- Amend `notes/sg2-benchmark-preregistration.md` §2 (the\n  \"publish-the-loss-regime\" commitment) — significant doc change;\n  track separately.\n- Update SG5 publication plan (bn-3ctu) to reflect \"maw broadly\n  dominates\" framing — SG5 territory.\n- Add a positive-framing \"why maw is the right default\" section\n  to the crib intro — could be its own bone if the affirmative\n  framing wants to be more than a line.\n\nPredecessors: bn-1t17 (the crib implementation).\nDoes NOT block: bn-3uj4 (v1.0-pre.1 cut) — crib wording is a\ntext correction, not a code or layout change. Pre.1 should ship\nwith the correct wording, but it's not gating.\n","kind":"task","labels":["ergonomics","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"s","title":"Realign maw crib: drop overkill-line, frame maw as the workspace tool (replaces worktrees)"}	blake3:zpm31yJkuN3Ptu5IFxZz-Y9QtprzHyzHiWtAHWy0g4g
