1779913487926180	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy5RE		item.create	bn-205s	{"description":"2026-05-27 lead direction: run more evals (Plan D) to actually settle\nthe overkill-regime question. Currently both bench bins hardcode\n`pilot_grid` (2 cells: C0 + C4). The full `spectrum_grid` (10 cells:\n5 T0 across C0..C4 + 5 T1..T5 chaos overlays at C2) is defined in\n`crates/maw-bench-sweep/src/grid.rs::spectrum_grid()` but unreachable\nfrom the CLI.\n\nAcceptance:\n1. New `--grid=pilot|spectrum` flag on:\n   - `crates/maw-bench-sweep/src/bin/sg2_sweep_pilot.rs`\n   - `crates/maw-bench-sweep/src/bin/sg3_layout_eval.rs` (if applicable —\n     sg3 may be cell-specific per bn-iux4 §1.3; if so, document why\n     --grid doesn't apply and skip).\n   Default: `pilot` (back-compat with existing recipes).\n2. New Justfile recipes (additive):\n   - `sg2-sweep-spectrum n='10' arm='maw' dir=''` — full 10-cell sweep.\n   - Keeps `sg2-sweep-pilot` + `sg2-sweep-real` recipes unchanged.\n3. Tests:\n   - sg2-sweep-pilot with `--grid=spectrum` drives 10 cells (assert\n     cell-count in test output or stderr).\n   - Default invocation still uses pilot_grid.\n4. cargo check + cargo test --workspace + cargo clippy --workspace\n   --all-targets -- -D warnings — all green.\n\nNon-goals:\n- Running the actual spectrum sweep (that's the calendar eval blast\n  after this lands).\n- Modifying the spectrum_grid definition itself.\n\nCoordination: parallel-dispatched with bn-3w0c (model axis) and\nbn-3hzt (chaos). All three touch Justfile + bin files; merge-time\nreconciliation handled by lead.\n\nPredecessors: bn-1h4b (eval-bin wire-up).\nDoes NOT block pre.1: bn-3uj4 doesn't need spectrum coverage to ship.\n","kind":"task","labels":["benchmark","v1-0"],"parent":"bn-142y","size":"xs","title":"Add --grid=pilot|spectrum flag to sg2-sweep-pilot + sg3-layout-eval (expose the full 10-cell spectrum)"}	blake3:h8-5W2eXzaQsmDD8waQwMVyyHijk9WfqMCIh2MUSBK4
